{"title_page": "KAT-TUN", "text_new": "{{More citations needed|date=April 2009}}\n{{Infobox musical artist <!-- For groups; see Wikipedia:WikiProject_Musicians -->\n| name             = KAT-TUN\n| image            = \n| alt              = \n| caption          = \n| image_size       = \n| background       =  group_or_band\n| alias            = \n| origin           = [[Tokyo]]\n| genre            = {{flatlist| \n* [[J-pop]]\n* [[rock music|rock]]}}\n| years_active     = {{Start date|2001}}\u2013present\n| label            = {{flatlist|\n* [[J Storm|J-One Records]]\n* [[J Storm]]}}\n| associated_acts  = \n| website = {{URL|www.j-storm.co.jp/kat-tun|J Storm}}<br />[https://www.johnnys-net.jp/page?id=artistTop&artist=14&lang=en_us Johnny's Net]\n| current_members  = \n* [[Kazuya Kamenashi]]\n* [[Yuichi Nakamaru]]\n* [[Tatsuya Ueda]]\n| past_members     = \n* [[Jin Akanishi]]\n* [[Koki Tanaka]]\n* [[Junnosuke Taguchi]]\n}}\n\n{{nihongo|'''KAT-TUN'''|\u30ab\u30c8\u30a5\u30fc\u30f3|Kat\u016bn}} is a Japanese [[boy band]] formed under [[Johnny & Associates]] (Johnny's) in 2001. The group's name was originally an acronym based on the first letter of each member's [[family name]]: [[Kazuya Kamenashi|Kazuya '''K'''amenashi]], [[Jin Akanishi|Jin '''A'''kanishi]], [[Junnosuke Taguchi|Junnosuke '''T'''aguchi]], [[Koki Tanaka|Koki '''T'''anaka]], [[Tatsuya Ueda|Tatsuya '''U'''eda]], and [[Yuichi Nakamaru|Yuichi '''N'''akamaru]]. Their debut on March 22, 2006 was marked by a [[wikt:tripartite|tripartite]] release of a [[CD single]], [[album]] and music DVD on their exclusive record label [[J Storm|J-One Records]]. Since then, all of their single, album and music DVD releases have debuted at number one on the ''[[Oricon]]'' music and DVD charts.\n\nIn 2010, Akanishi left the group to start a solo career, making the group's acronym then come from '''KA'''menashi, '''T'''aguchi, '''T'''anaka, '''U'''eda, and '''N'''akamaru, and the group toured with five members.<ref name=\"akanishi_solo\">{{cite web|url=http://www.tokyograph.com/news/id-6357|title=Johnny to remove Akanishi from KAT-TUN|date=2010-07-16|publisher=Tokyograph|accessdate=2010-07-29}}</ref> In 2013, Tanaka's contract was terminated for several violations, leaving KAT-TUN as a four-man ensemble, and '''T'''atsuya '''U'''eda took the T to keep the acronym.<ref name=tanakaout>{{cite web|url=http://natalie.mu/music/news/101091 |title=\u30ca\u30bf\u30ea\u30fc - KAT-TUN\u7530\u4e2d\u8056\u3001\u4e8b\u52d9\u6240\u5951\u7d04\u89e3\u9664\u3067\u30b0\u30eb\u30fc\u30d7\u8131\u9000 |publisher=Natalie.mu |date=2013-10-09 |accessdate=2013-10-09}}</ref> By the end of March 2016, Taguchi left both the group and the agency, leaving KAT-TUN with only three remaining members.\n\n==History==\n\n===2001\u20132005: Formation and pre-debut activities===\nBefore becoming KAT-TUN, each member belonged to different [[Johnny's Jr|trainee]] units within Johnny & Associates. In 2001, eight members were chosen to become a temporary dancing unit in order to support [[Koichi Domoto]] in the [[NHK]] music program, ''Pop Jam''. The eight members were switched around before it officially became KAT-TUN, with the current three members plus Jin Akanishi, Koki Tanaka and Junnosuke Taguchi. Although the formation was only meant to be a temporary support unit, KAT-TUN gained a great deal of attention and became a solid unit.<ref>{{cite web|last=Greenburg|first=Adam|url={{Allmusic|class=artist|id=p814258|pure_url=yes}}|title=KAT-TUN: Biography|publisher=[[Allmusic]]|accessdate=2010-04-18}}</ref>\n\nIn 2002, in response to many requests, KAT-TUN held their first concert called {{nihongo|3=Okyaku-sama wa Kami-summer - Concert 55man Nin Ai no Request ni Kotaete!!|2=\u304a\u5ba2\u69d8\u306f\u795e\u30b5\u30de\u30fcConcert 55\u4e07\u4eba\u611b\u306e\u30ea\u30af\u30a8\u30b9\u30c8\u306b\u5fdc\u3048\u3066!!}}, for which 550,000 people tried to get tickets.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cdjapan.co.jp/detailview.html?KEY=JEBN-19|title=Okyakusama wa Kamisama - Concert 55man nin Ai no request ni kotaete!!|publisher=CDJapan|accessdate=2010-04-18}}</ref> That same year, they performed eleven shows in a single day. This is the current record in Japan for the most performances in one day. Since then, KAT-TUN has held concerts in Japan almost every season.\n\nIn 2003-2004, their popularity rose to that of a debuted group, to the point where they performed on [[Music Station]] multiple times before debuting. In 2005, KAT-TUN released their first major DVD, {{nihongo|3=KAT-TUN Live Kaizokuban|2=KAT-TUN Live\u6d77\u8cca\u5e06|4=lit. KAT-TUN Live: Pirate Sails}}, which topped the ''Oricon'' yearly chart for the best-selling DVD. At the 20th [[Japan Gold Disc Award]]s, ''Live Kaizokuban'' placed on the Music Video Of The Year list.<ref name=\"jpgold2006\" />\n\n===2006: Debut and \"Real Face\"===\nOn March 22, KAT-TUN released their debut single \"[[Real Face]]\", accompanied by an album, ''Best of KAT-TUN'' and a DVD ''Real Face Film''. These were released on their own label [[J-One Records]]. The group also went on a nationwide tour, ''Live of KAT-TUN \"Real Face\"'', in support of the album. Within the first week, ''Best of KAT-TUN'', \"Real Face\" and ''Real Face Film'' topped all three ''Oricon'' weekly charts by selling 556,548 copies, 754,234 copies and 374,202 copies respectively.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.oricon.co.jp/news/ranking/16719/|title=KAT-TUN\u30013\u51a0\u9054\u6210\uff01\u30b7\u30f3\u30b0\u30eb\u3001\u30a2\u30eb\u30d0\u30e0\u3001DVD\u3001\u540c\u6642\u5236\u8987\uff01|publisher=[[Oricon]]|accessdate=2010-04-18|language=Japanese}}</ref> They became the second artists to do so, the first being [[Ayumi Hamasaki]]. With these numbers, KAT-TUN holds the record for the highest weekly single debut sales (previously held by [[Arashi]] with their debut single \"[[Arashi (song)|Arashi]]\" of 557,000 copies sold in 1999).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.oricon.co.jp/music/special/060322_02.html|title=KAT-TUN \u6ce8\u76ee\u306e\u30a2\u30fc\u30c6\u30a3\u30b9\u30c8\u9042\u306b\u30c7\u30d3\u30e5\u30fc\uff01|publisher=[[Oricon]]|accessdate=2010-04-18|language=Japanese}}</ref> In addition, \"Real Face\" topped the ''Oricon'' charts for three weeks straight, becoming the first debut single to do so in Japan in 8 years 8 months since [[KinKi Kids]]' debut single \"Garasu no Sh\u014dnen.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.oricon.co.jp/news/ranking/18199/|title=KAT-TUN\u300100\u5e74\u4ee3\u30c7\u30d3\u30e5\u30fc\u30fb\u30a2\u30fc\u30c6\u30a3\u30b9\u30c8\u521d\u306e\u5feb\u6319\u9054\u6210\uff01|publisher=[[Oricon]]|date=2006-04-10|accessdate=2010-04-18|language=Japanese}}</ref> The single sold over a million copies in nine weeks, making \"Real Face\" the highest selling single for the year 2006.<ref name=\"year2006\">[http://www.oricon.co.jp/music/special/061221_02.html ''Oricon'' Ranking 2006] 2006. Retrieved November 10, 2009. {{in lang|ja}}</ref>\n\nIn March 2006, KAT-TUN became the first group to hold their own performances in Japan's most popular stadium, [[Tokyo Dome]], before debuting. They performed to 110,000 people over two days and about 630,000 people in total during the tour. About three months after releasing \"Real Face\", KAT-TUN released their second single, \"[[Signal (KAT-TUN song)|Signal]]\", on July 19.\n\nOn October 12, member Akanishi announced a hiatus from the group in order to study linguistics abroad in the United States, leaving KAT-TUN as a five-member group for six months.<ref>{{cite web|title=KAT-TUN's Jin Akanishi takes break from KAT-TUN; goes to America for English studies|url=http://www.tokyograph.com/news/id-187}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=KAT-TUN's Jin Akanishi back in Japan|url=http://www.tokyograph.com/news/id-928}}</ref> The remaining members continued activities by releasing their third single, \"[[Bokura no Machi de]]\" as the theme song to members Kamenashi and Tanaka's drama, ''[[Tatta Hitotsu no Koi]]'' and their second album, ''Cartoon KAT-TUN II You'' on December 7.\n\nKAT-TUN is the first group in Japan to have all three singles from debut to exceed 500,000 in yearly sales, taking first, fifth and thirteenth place on the Oricon yearly singles chart.<ref name=\"year2006\" />\n\n===2007: ''Cartoon KAT-TUN II You''===\nUnder the same name as their second album, KAT-TUN started their second nationwide tour, ''Tour 2007 Cartoon KAT-TUN II You'', still without Akanishi, on April 3. The next day, KAT-TUN began to host their own variety show ''[[Cartoon KAT-TUN]]'', which aired every Wednesday from 11:55&nbsp;p.m. to 12:26&nbsp;a.m.\n\nAkanishi returned to Japan on April 19 and officially resumed work activities on April 20.<ref>[http://www.tokyograph.com/news/id-928 Tokyograph: Akanishi Back In Japan] April 19, 2007. Retrieved December 18, 2007.</ref> Akanishi joined the rest of KAT-TUN during their tour on April 21 in [[Sendai]] for the encore, marking his official return to KAT-TUN.\n\nOn June 6, KAT-TUN released their fourth single, \"[[Yorokobi no Uta]]\", as the theme song to Tanaka's drama, ''Tokkyu Tanaka 3 Go''.\n\nOn November 21, they simultaneously released their fifth single, \"[[Keep the Faith (KAT-TUN song)|Keep the Faith]]\", as the theme song to members Akanishi and Taguchi's drama, ''[[Yukan Club]]'', and the DVD to their ''Tokyo Dome Live of KAT-TUN \"Real Face\"'' concert. The DVD marked their fifth consecutive release topping the Oricon musical DVD chart, and set the opening week record for the year.<ref>[http://www.oricon.co.jp/news/rankmusic/49982/ ''Oricon'' Style: KAT-TUN\u3001\u65b0\u66f2\u3067\u4eca\u5e74\u306e\u521d\u52d5\u6700\u9ad8\u8a18\u9332\u9054\u6210] November 27, 2007. Retrieved December 23, 2007. {{in lang|ja}}</ref> KAT-TUN took the annual number one position on the Oricon musical DVD charts for the third time in a row with the release.\n\nAfter KinKi Kids, KAT-TUN is the second artist to have all singles since debut to exceed 300,000 in sales during their first week.<ref>[http://www.tokyograph.com/news/id-2141 Tokyograph: KAT-TUN sets 2007 record, L'Arc returns to top] November 6, 2007. Retrieved December 23, 2007.</ref>\n\n===2008: ''Queen of Pirates''===\nKAT-TUN released 'Lips', the theme song to Kamenashi's drama based on the [[manga]] ''[[One Pound Gospel]]'', as their sixth single on February 6.<ref>[http://www.johnnys-net.jp/j/artists/kattun/disco/disco_single.html Johnny's Net: KAT-TUN Discography] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304003005/http://www.johnnys-net.jp/j/artists/kattun/disco/disco_single.html |date=2016-03-04 }} December 21, 2007. Retrieved December 23, 2007. {{in lang|ja}}</ref> The single topped at number one on the Oricon charts.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.oricon.co.jp/search/result.php?kbn=js&types=rnk&year=2008&month=2&week=3&submit4.x=5&submit4.y=19|script-title=ja:2008\u5e7402\u6708\u7b2c3\u9031\u306e\u30b7\u30f3\u30b0\u30eb\u30e9\u30f3\u30ad\u30f3\u30b0\u60c5\u5831|publisher=[[Oricon]]|accessdate=2010-04-18|language=Japanese}}</ref>\n\nKAT-TUN released their seventh single \"[[Don't U Ever Stop]]\" on May 14, which topped the weekly ''Oricon'' chart. On May 15, during the MC segment promoting \"Don't U Ever Stop\" on [[Music Station]], Kamenashi announced that two shows had been added to their Tokyo Dome tourdates, resulting in a total of four consecutive days at the Dome. This marked a historic event in the Dome's history, as KAT-TUN became the first Japanese artist to hold four consecutive days at the stadium since it opened in 1988.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tokyograph.com/news/id-4328|title=KAT-TUN takes over Tokyo Dome for a week|date=2009-01-23|publisher=Tokyograph|accessdate=2010-04-18}}</ref> Other Japanese artists, such as [[SMAP]], [[X Japan]] and [[Ayumi Hamasaki]] have had three consecutive days at the Dome. The Rolling Stones and Michael Jackson have played multiple days at the Dome, but they were not consecutive.\n\nOn June 4, KAT-TUN released their third album, ''[[KAT-TUN III: Queen of Pirates]]''.\n\nOn December 3, KAT-TUN released \"[[White X'mas (song)|White X'mas]]\", their first Christmas single.\n\nOn December 21, it was announced that KAT-TUN would release a new single \"[[One Drop (KAT-TUN song)|One Drop]]\" as a tie-in theme song to Kamenashi's new drama, [[Kami no Shizuku (TV series)|Kami no Shizuku]], just two months after their \"White X'mas\" single. The release consisted of three versions: Limited Edition w/DVD, Regular Edition (First Press) and a Regular Edition.\n\n===2010: International activities, Akanishi's departure and ''No More Pain''===\nOn February 10, KAT-TUN released their first single since March 2009, which was used for Kamenashi's live-action drama adaptation of Tomoko Hayakawa's manga series ''[[Yamato Nadeshiko Shichi Henge]]'', which premiered January 15 on [[Tokyo Broadcasting System|TBS]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Kazuya Kamenashi gets lead role in new TBS winter drama for 2010|url=http://www.tokyograph.com/news/id-5516}}</ref> The single, \"[[Love Yourself (Kimi ga Kirai na Kimi ga Suki)]]\", debuted at number one on the Oricon weekly singles chart, resulting in KAT-TUN's eleventh consecutive number one single since their debut.<ref>{{cite web|title=KAT-TUN's 11th consecutive number one single|url=http://www.tokyograph.com/news/id-5811}}</ref> It became KAT-TUN's first single to sell more than 350,000 copies in its first week since the May 2008 release of their single \"[[Don't U Ever Stop]]\", which sold more than 381,000 copies in its first week.<ref>{{cite web|title=KAT-TUN tops the Oricon weekly charts with their 11th consecutive number one single |url=http://smash.music.yahoo.co.jp/top/20100215-00000032-oric-ent/ }}{{dead link|date=April 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n\nOn March 24, Johnny & Associates announced that KAT-TUN would go on their first Asia concert tour as a five-member group while Akanishi held his own solo concerts in the United States, making him the first Johnny's artist to perform solo in the United States.<ref>{{cite web|title=KAT-TUN 2010 World Tour|url=http://www.sponichi.co.jp/entertainment/news/2010/03/25/01.html|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100327092059/http://www.sponichi.co.jp/entertainment/news/2010/03/25/01.html|archivedate=2010-03-27}}</ref> KAT-TUN is set to have their Asia Tour from early May to late August and although the majority of the concerts will be held in Japan, KAT-TUN will also be heading to Bangkok on July 31, Seoul from August 6 to 7, and Taipei from August 27 to 28; other sources say that a Hawaii concert is also being considered.<ref>{{cite web|title=Jin Akanishi to go to L.A while the rest of the members go on an Asia Tour|url=http://www.tokyograph.com/news/id-5944}}</ref> Due to his absence from KAT-TUN's Asia concert tour and single promotions, Akanishi did not participate in the recording of KAT-TUN's twelfth single \"[[Going!]]\" set for release on May 12.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tokyograph.com/news/id-5989|title=Next KAT-TUN single to lack Akanishi|date=2010-04-06|publisher=Tokyograph|accessdate=2010-04-18}}</ref> Due to the [[2010 Thai political protests|political unrest in Thailand]], Johnny & Associates announced on May 15 that KAT-TUN's concert in Bangkok would be indefinitely postponed.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tokyograph.com/news/id-6104|title=KAT-TUN cancels Bangkok concert|date=2010-05-15|publisher=Tokyograph|accessdate=2010-05-16}}</ref>\n\nKAT-TUN released their first 2010 album, ''[[No More Pain]]'', on June 16 in two versions: a limited and regular edition that both include solo songs by each member.<ref name=\"cdj\">{{cite web|url=http://www.cdjapan.co.jp/detailview.html?KEY=JACA-5224|title=<nowiki>No More Pain [w/ DVD, Limited Edition]</nowiki>|work=CDJapan|accessdate=2010-06-23}}</ref> The limited edition contains thirteen songs and a bonus DVD with the PVs and making-of's the album's songs while the regular edition contains a bonus track.<ref name=\"cdj\" />\n\nJohnny & Associates announced on July 17 that Akanishi would leave the group in late 2010 to pursue a solo career while the rest of the members would continue to work as a five-member group.<ref name=\"akanishi_solo\" /> On July 21, Akanishi himself confirmed through the official Johnny's mobile site, Johnny's Web, that he would leave KAT-TUN to focus on his solo career,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tokyograph.com/news/id-6372|title=Akanishi comments on leaving KAT-TUN|date=2010-07-20|publisher=Tokyograph|accessdate=2010-07-29}}</ref> although he had not appeared on any event to his fans until October.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tokyograph.com/news/id-6724|title=Jin Akanishi aims for simultaneous release in U.S., Japan|date=2010-10-03|publisher=Tokyograph|accessdate=2010-10-03}}</ref>\n\nKAT-TUN continued as a group of five. On August 28, the last day of their World Big Tour 2010, KAT-TUN revealed their 2011 tour plan to celebrate their fifth anniversary by performing at industrial complexes in five cities in Japan and expanding its overseas tour to five different countries including Korea, Taiwan, Thailand, China, and Hawaii.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sanspo.com/geino/news/100828/gng1008280505001-n2.htm|title=\uff2b\uff21\uff34\uff0d\uff34\uff35\uff2e\u4e0a\u7530\u3001\u8131\u81fc\uff01\u6551\u6025\u8eca\u3067\u642c\u9001, Japan|date=2010-08-29|publisher=Sanspo|accessdate=2010-08-30|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100830192231/http://www.sanspo.com/geino/news/100828/gng1008280505001-n2.htm|archivedate=2010-08-30}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://headlines.yahoo.co.jp/hl?a=20100828-00000046-spn-ent |title=\uff2b\uff21\uff34\uff0d\uff34\uff35\uff2e\u3000\u5de5\u696d\u5730\u57df\u3067\u30b3\u30f3\u30b5\u30fc\u30c8\u8a08\u753b\uff1f, Japan |date=2010-08-29 |publisher=Sponichi Annex |accessdate=2010-08-30 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100905230931/http://headlines.yahoo.co.jp/hl?a=20100828-00000046-spn-ent |archivedate=September 5, 2010 }}</ref> The Hawaii concert would make them the first Johnny artist to hold a concert in Hawaii.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://hochi.yomiuri.co.jp/entertainment/news/20100828-OHT1T00023.htm|title=\uff2b\uff21\uff34\u2015\uff34\uff35\uff2e\u3001\u6765\u590f\u306b\u30b3\u30f3\u30d3\u30ca\u30fc\u30c8\u30e9\u30a4\u30d6\u8a08\u753b, Japan|date=2010-08-29|publisher=Yomiuri|accessdate=2010-08-30|language=Japanese|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100829201650/http://hochi.yomiuri.co.jp/entertainment/news/20100828-OHT1T00023.htm|archivedate=2010-08-29}}</ref> The World Big Tour is where former member Tanaka Koki gave the name \"hyphens\" to the fans, saying that the fans unite KAT-TUN together.\n\nOn October 13, KAT-TUN announced the release of their new single, \"Change Ur World\", which was KAT-TUN's 13th single and the first single after Akanishi's official departure, was released on November 17.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.johnnys-net.jp/j/artists/kattun/disco/_popup/pop_c_ur_w.html|title=Change Ur World Information Page, Japan|date=2010-10-13|publisher=Johnny's net|accessdate=2010-10-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101025002329/http://www.johnnys-net.jp/j/artists/kattun/disco/_popup/pop_c_ur_w.html|archive-date=2010-10-25|url-status=dead}}</ref>  The single debuted at number one on the Oricon weekly singles chart for selling 230,829 copies, resulting in KAT-TUN's thirteenth consecutive number one single since their debut plus all of their 13 singles sold over 200,000 copies in the first week.<ref>{{cite web|title=\u3010\u30aa\u30ea\u30b3\u30f3\u3011KAT-TUN\u3001\u30c7\u30d3\u30e5\u30fc\u304b\u308913\u4f5c\u9023\u7d9a\u30b7\u30f3\u30b0\u30eb\u9996\u4f4d, Japan|date=2010-11-23|publisher=Oricon|accessdate=2010-12-03|url=http://www.oricon.co.jp/news/rankmusic/82302/full/?cat_id=tw|language=Japanese}}</ref>\n\nOn December 29, KAT-TUN released KAT-TUN -NO MORE PAI\u0418- WORLD TOUR 2010 DVD, featuring their last day in Japan leg of their successful World Big Tour 2010 at Kyocera Dome and more concert footages from their Korea and Taiwan legs.<ref>{{cite web|title=KAT-TUN -NO MORE PAI\u0418- WORLD TOUR 2010 DVD Information, Japan|date=2010-12-10|publisher=J-Storm|accessdate=2010-12-11|url=http://www.j-storm.co.jp/kat_tun/disco/dvd/d_06.html|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101208232504/http://www.j-storm.co.jp/kat_tun/disco/dvd/d_06.html|archivedate=2010-12-08}}</ref>\n\n===2011: 5th anniversary===\nThe group announced a release of their 14th single on 2010s Christmas Eve, \"Ultimate Wheels\" on February 2, 2011 along with a tie-in CM of Suzuki Solio car that the group endorsed.<ref>{{cite web|title=Ultimate Wheels Information, Japan|date=2010-12-24|publisher=Johnny's Net|accessdate=2010-12-25|url=http://www.johnnys-net.jp/j/artists/kattun/disco/_popup/pop_ultimate_wheels.html|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101229080513/http://www.johnnys-net.jp/j/artists/kattun/disco/_popup/pop_ultimate_wheels.html|archive-date=2010-12-29|url-status=dead}}</ref> On January 6, KAT-TUN announced its plan of KAT-TUN Live Tour 2011 during May to October. The tour includes the 5 big dome tour at Sapporo Dome, Tokyo Dome, Nagoya Dome, Yahoo Dome in Fukuoka, and Kyocera Dome in Osaka and a special live event in Kawasaki on July 17\u201319. KAT-TUN will become the fourth Johnny group to be able to conquer the 5 big domes in Japan after SMAP, KinKi Kids and Arashi. After October, the group will start their Asia Tour that includes Thailand, Taiwan, and Korea.<ref>{{cite web|title=\u300c\uff2b\uff21\uff34\u2015\uff34\uff35\uff2e\u300d\u53f2\u4e0a\u521d\u306e\u30b3\u30f3\u30d3\u30ca\u30fc\u30c8\u516c\u6f14, Japan|date=2011-01-06|publisher=Sponichi Annex|accessdate=2011-01-15|url=http://www.sponichi.co.jp/entertainment/news/2011/01/06/01.html|language=Japanese|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110110022732/http://www.sponichi.co.jp/entertainment/news/2011/01/06/01.html|archivedate=2011-01-10}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=\uff2b\uff21\uff34\u2015\uff34\uff35\uff2e\u30e9\u30f3\u30c9\uff01\uff17\u6708\u5ddd\u5d0e\u306b\u51fa\u73fe, Japan|date=2011-01-06|publisher=Yomiuri|accessdate=2011-01-15|url=http://hochi.yomiuri.co.jp/entertainment/news/20110106-OHT1T00038.htm|language=Japanese|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110108193810/http://hochi.yomiuri.co.jp/entertainment/news/20110106-OHT1T00038.htm|archivedate=2011-01-08}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=\uff2b\uff21\uff34\u2010\uff34\uff35\uff2e\u56fd\u5185\u521d\uff01\u30b3\u30f3\u30d3\u30ca\u30fc\u30c8\u30e9\u30a4\u30d6, Japan|date=2011-01-06|publisher=Daily Sports Online|accessdate=2011-01-15|url=http://www.daily.co.jp/gossip/johnnys_topics/2011/01/06/0003720132.shtm|language=Japanese}}{{dead link|date=January 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=\uff2b\uff21\uff34\uff0d\uff34\uff35\uff2e\u521d\u91ce\u5916\u306f\u4eac\u6d5c\u5de5\u696d\u5730\u5e2f, Japan|date=2011-01-06|publisher=Nikkan Sports|accessdate=2011-01-15|url=http://www.nikkansports.com/entertainment/news/p-et-tp0-20110106-721431.html|language=Japanese}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=\u72ac\u9023\u308c\uff2f\uff2b\uff01\uff2b\uff21\uff34\uff0d\uff34\uff35\uff2e\u7279\u5927\u30a4\u30d9\u30f3\u30c8, Japan|date=2011-01-06|publisher=Sanspo|accessdate=2011-01-15|url=http://www.sanspo.com/geino/news/110106/gng1101060505001-n1.htm|language=Japanese|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110108171236/http://www.sanspo.com/geino/news/110106/gng1101060505001-n1.htm|archivedate=2011-01-08}}</ref> \"Ultimate Wheels\" became their 14th straight No.1 single since their debut. The total number of copies sold in the first week was over 180,000 copies, reported by Oricon. Early March, KAT-TUN announced three new songs in three days, including \"Perfect\" for Kamenashi's new Aoki TV commercial,<ref>{{cite web|title=Perfect song information, Japan|date=2011-03-03|publisher=Johnny's Net|accessdate=2011-03-03|url=http://www.johnnys-net.jp/j/artists/kattun/info_110303.html|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110307220114/http://www.johnnys-net.jp/j/artists/kattun/info_110303.html|archive-date=2011-03-07|url-status=dead}}</ref> \"White\" for a Sofina commercial,<ref>{{cite web|title=Perfect song information, Japan|date=2011-02-18|publisher=Johnny's Net|accessdate=2011-03-03|url=http://www.johnnys-net.jp/j/artists/kattun/info_110218.html|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110219234546/http://www.johnnys-net.jp/j/artists/kattun/info_110218.html|archive-date=2011-02-19|url-status=dead}}</ref> and \"Diamond\" as the theme song of NTV telecasts of Yomiuri Giants baseball games.\n\nIt was announced on March 29 that Johnny's Company would start a new charity project called Marching J, a fundraising project for the Tohoku earthquake victims. The first part of the project started as an event held from April 1 through April 3. From the company, [[SMAP]], [[Tokio (band)|Tokio]], [[KinKi Kids]], [[V6]], [[Arashi]], [[Tackey and Tsubasa]], [[News (band)|NEWS]], [[Kanjani8]], KAT-TUN, [[Hey! Say! JUMP]] and some Johnny's Juniors participated in this first event. The first event will be held at Tokyo, in front of the first Yoyogi gymnasium. Groups took turns according to their schedule and will have a talk session in front of the fans, also calling out for donations for the earthquake victims. And due to this disaster, all the planned events to celebrate KAT-TUN's 5th debut anniversary were cancelled.\n\nOn May 18, KAT-TUN's 15th single, \"White\", was released with \"Perfect\" as its coupling song. By this time, they also announced another two new songs, \"Cosmic Child\" for a Wing TV commercial,<ref>{{cite web|title=Cosmic Child song information, Japan|date=2011-05-17|publisher=Johnny's Net|accessdate=2011-05-17|url=http://www.johnnys-net.jp/j/artists/kattun/info_110511.html|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110516053023/http://www.johnnys-net.jp/j/artists/kattun/info_110511.html|archive-date=2011-05-16|url-status=dead}}</ref> and \"Run For You\" for a New Suzuki Solio commercial.<ref>{{cite web|title=Run For You song information, Japan|date=2011-02-17|publisher=Johnny's Net|accessdate=2011-05-17|url=http://www.johnnys-net.jp/j/artists/kattun/index.html|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100521154302/http://www.johnnys-net.jp/j/artists/kattun/index.html|archive-date=2010-05-21|url-status=dead}}</ref> On May 29, KAT-TUN with all its five members joined another Marching J project, \"Johnny's Charity Baseball Tournament\" with other Johnny artists and juniors at Tokyo Dome, in which the ticket sales would be donated for Japan's earthquake and tsunami victims.<ref>{{cite web|title=Johnny's Charty Baseball Tournament Information, Japan|date=2011-05-28|publisher=Johnny's Net|accessdate=2011-05-28|url=http://www.johnnys-net.jp/j/artists/kattun/consta/consta.html|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110524191212/http://www.johnnys-net.jp/j/artists/kattun/consta/consta.html|archive-date=2011-05-24|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nIt was announced in mid-June that members Kazuya Kamenashi, Koki Tanaka and Yuichi Nakamaru would star in this year's ''Dream Boy'' musicals as the leads, shows will commence from September 3 to 25.<ref>{{cite web|title=KAT-TUN\u3001\"\u52dd\u904b\"\u306b\u6539\u540d!?|date=2011-06-14|publisher=Oricon|accessdate=2011-08-19|url=http://www.oricon.co.jp/news/confidence/88808/full}}</ref>\n\nOn September 8, 2011, it was confirmed that KAT-TUN would host a new TV show titled ''[[KAT-TUN no Zettai Manetaku Naru TV]]'', their first show since ''[[Cartoon KAT-TUN]]'' ended in March 2010. The new show began airing on October 18 on NTV.<ref>{{cite web|title=KAT-TUN to host new variety show|date=2011-09-08|publisher=Tokyograph|accessdate=2011-09-15|url=http://www.tokyograph.com/news/kat-tun-to-host-new-variety-show}}</ref> During the broadcast of the first episode, it was revealed that the show will only air for a limited time until the end of December 2011 with a total of 10 episodes.<ref>{{cite web|title=Zettai Manetakunaru TV air for 10 episodes |date=2011-10-18 |publisher=KTnewsinfo |accessdate=2011-11-01 |url=http://kt-newsinfo.livejournal.com/98288.html |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121119003122/http://kt-newsinfo.livejournal.com/98288.html |archivedate=2012-11-19 }}</ref> \nOn September 30, 2011, KAT-TUN announced their 17th single \"Birth\" as the soundtrack to Kamenashi Kazuya's drama \"Youkai Ningen Bem\" would have been released on November 30. \"Birth\" became their 17th straight No.1 single on the Oricon's weekly chart since their debut.\n\n===2012: ''Chain''===\nKAT-TUN began their new year with an extreme special TV show titled ''KAT-TUN no Sekaiichi Dame Yoru Ni'', a one-off show broadcast on the night of January 1 on TBS. A few weeks later they announced the release of their sixth album, titled ''Chain'', scheduled for releasing on February 22. On January 13, KAT-TUN endorsed the mobile game site Entag which used KAT-TUN's album track \"Smile for You\" as the commercial song and the first-ever KAT-TUN animation, \"Ai wa KAT-TUN\", voiced by KAT-TUN themselves, was launched on The Entag site for a limited period.<ref>{{cite web|title=KAT-TUN\u306e\u30c6\u30ec\u30d3CM\u3068\u30aa\u30ea\u30b8\u30ca\u30eb\u30a2\u30cb\u30e1\u304c\u9650\u5b9a\u914d\u4fe1\u3000\u30e2\u30d0\u30a4\u30eb\u30b2\u30fc\u30e0\u30b5\u30a4\u30c8\"entag!\"\u306e\u30b5\u30fc\u30d3\u30b9\u304c\u9593\u3082\u306a\u304f\u958b\u59cb|date=2012-01-06|publisher=Famitsu|accessdate=2012-01-12|url=http://app.famitsu.com/20120106_19095/}}</ref> On February 11, they kicked off their nationwide tour \"KAT-TUN Live Tour 2012 Chain\". This tour covered 12 cities, including Sendai. The tour started in Niigata and will end in Sendai. They will become the first Johnnys group to perform in the affected areas after the earthquake and tsunami disaster.<ref>{{cite web|title=KAT-TUN LIVE TOUR 2012 CHAIN Information|date=2011-11-26|publisher=Johnny's Net|accessdate=2012-01-12|url=http://www.johnnys-net.jp/j/artists/kattun/consta/consta.html|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120118060945/http://www.johnnys-net.jp/j/artists/kattun/consta/consta.html|archive-date=2012-01-18|url-status=dead}}</ref> Music Station presented on Jan 13 with a special report for the 'Most Powerful Group BEST 20' which listed the Top 20 most powerful groups of all-time in terms of physical single and album sales, KAT-TUN was listed at number 16 with their five-year debut, 17 singles and 5 albums, together they have sold over 8,450,000 records. Music Station hints to this ranking included the debut single 'Real Face' which became 2006's number 1 selling single and how they managed to hold 8 consecutive concert at Tokyo Dome. Among the groups in Top 20, KAT-TUN is apparently the newest group on the list.<ref>{{cite web|title=KAT-TUN ranks No.16 Most Powerful Group of all-time |date=2012-01-14 |publisher=Kat-tunlove |accessdate=2012-02-09 |url=http://kattunlove.livejournal.com/7518329.html |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120115121714/http://kattunlove.livejournal.com/7518329.html |archivedate=2012-01-15 }}</ref>\n\nKAT-TUN's 6th studio album, \"CHAIN\", reached No.1 on Oricon album ranking on March 5, making them the first male artist in history to have six consecutive No.1 albums ever since the debut. KAT-TUN broke the record for the first time in 24 years and 10 months.<ref>{{cite web|title=KAT-TUN\u306e\u6700\u65b0\u30a2\u30eb\u30d0\u30e0\u9996\u4f4d\u3000\u7537\u6027\u6b4c\u624b\u521d\u306e\u30aa\u30ea\u30b8\u30ca\u30eb1st\u304b\u30896\u4f5c\u9023\u7d9a|date=2012-03-05|publisher=Oricon|accessdate=2012-03-05|url=http://www.oricon.co.jp/news/rankmusic/2007637/full}}</ref> On March 8, it was announced that a second episode of ''KAT-TUN no Sekaiichi Dame Yoru Ni'' will be aired on April 3.<ref>{{cite tweet|user=ori_suta|author=\u30aa\u30ea\u2605\u30b9\u30bf|number=177408904379105281|date=7 March 2012|title=\u300eKAT-TUN\u306e\u4e16\u754c\u4e00\u30c0\u30e1\u306a\u591c\u300f\u7b2c\u4e8c\u5f3e\u306e\u653e\u9001\u304c4\u67083\u65e5\u306b\u6c7a\u5b9a\uff01\u30e1\u30f3\u30d0\u30fc\u306e\u7686\u3055\u3093\u306b\u53d6\u6750\u3057\u3066\u304d\u307e\u3057\u305f\u3002\u7206\u7b11\u306e\u9023\u7d9a\u306e\u30a4\u30f3\u30bf\u30d3\u30e5\u30fc\u3067\u3057\u305f\u3088\u266a\u30aa\u30ea\u2605\u30b9\u30bf\u3067\u306f23\u65e5\u58f2\u306b\u30ed\u30b1\u5bc6\u7740\uff06\u6f14\u51fa\u306e\u30de\u30c3\u30b3\u30a4\u6589\u85e4\u3055\u3093\u3068\u30e1\u30f3\u30d0\u30fc\u306e\u5bfe\u8ac7\u300130\u65e5\u58f2\u3067\u30e1\u30f3\u30d0\u30fc\u306e\u30a4\u30f3\u30bf\u30d3\u30e5\u30fc\u3092\u304a\u5c4a\u3051\uff01\u3010\u30aa\u30ea\u30b9\u30bf\u7de8\u96c6\u90e8\uff0f\u307e\u3061\u3053\u3011}}</ref>\n\nOfficial confirmations for the upcoming 2012 shows for Johnny's long-running ''Dream Boys'' musicals was released, and once again member Kamenashi reprises his role as the main lead for the musical. According to confirmation, the shows will begin in September.<ref>{{cite web|title=Dream Boys 2012 confirmed |date=2012-03-12 |publisher=aramatheydidnt |accessdate=2012-03-14 |url=http://aramatheydidnt.livejournal.com/3521879.html |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120312095410/http://aramatheydidnt.livejournal.com/3521879.html |archivedate=2012-03-12 }}</ref> On April 20\u201322, KAT-TUN performed at Tokyo Dome as parts of their LIVE TOUR 2012 CHAIN tour. According to news reports, KAT-TUN's original idea \"Flash-Tree\" spotlights was introduced for the first time in Johnny and also Tokyo Dome's 25m moving stage was the longest in Johnny's history.<ref>{{cite web|title=Mezamashi News|date=2012-04-23|publisher=|url=}}</ref>\n\nOn June 27, KAT-TUN released its 18th single ''To The Limit'', which was used as a tie-up song for Suzuki Solio Bandit CM.  On June 29 Music Station reported that KAT-TUN ranked as No.10 best-selling Heisei era's idol with the total sales of 6,661,293 copies from 17 singles. In early August it was announced that KAT-TUN's ''Sekaiichi Dame Yoru Ni'' TV special will be turned into a regular show due to the success of the previous 2 special episodes. The regular show was renamed [[KAT-TUN Sekaiichi dame na yoru!]] and began airing on August 24 on TBS.<ref>{{cite web|title=Info on new KAT-TUN regular TV series |date=2012-08-10 |publisher=aramatheydidnt |accessdate=2012-09-17 |url=http://aramatheydidnt.livejournal.com/4129788.html |archive-url=https://archive.is/20121204005707/http://aramatheydidnt.livejournal.com/4129788.html |url-status=dead |archive-date=2012-12-04 }}</ref>\n\nKAT-TUN's 19th single \"Fumetsu no Scrum\" which was used as the themesong for [[Kanjani8]] member Yasuda Shota's drama [[Dragon Seinendan]], was released on September 12 and sold around 157,000 copies within its first week of release, this gives KAT-TUN their 19th consecutive #1 single since their debut in 2006.<ref>{{cite web|title=KAT-TUN grabs No.1 spot on Oricon weekly chart|date=2012-09-17|publisher=tokyohive|accessdate=2012-09-18|url=http://www.tokyohive.com/2012/09/kat-tun-grabs-no-1-spot-on-oricon-weekly-chart/}}</ref>\nIn November, KAT-TUN achieved their 9th consecutive no.1 music-DVD, and 8th no.1 overall DVD with their live DVD, \"KAT-TUN LIVE TOUR 2012 CHAIN TOKYO DOME.\" The latter achievement puts them at 3rd place among male groups who have done the most no.1 overall DVDs in history after B'z and Mr.Children.<ref>{{cite web|title=KAT-TUN\u304cB\u2019z\u30fbMr.Children\u306e\u8a18\u9332\u306b\u4e26\u3093\u3060!!|date=2012-11-28|publisher=oricon|accessdate=2013-01-13|url=http://onlystar.oricon.co.jp/news/music/1959/|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20130218181747/http://onlystar.oricon.co.jp/news/music/1959/|archivedate=2013-02-18}}</ref>\n\n===2013: Tanaka Koki's departure===\n\"Expose\" sold 155,000 copies in first weeks. With this single, their number of consecutive singles topping the chart has reached 20. KAT-TUN is the second artist to top the single chart for 20 consecutive singles since the debut. It was only achieved by their senior KinKi Kids 8 years and a month ago with \u201cAnniversary\u201d.<ref>{{cite web|author=|url=http://www.tokyohive.com/2013/02/kat-tun-tops-oricon-weekly-chart-for-20-consecutive-singles-since-their-debut-single/ |title=KAT-TUN tops Oricon weekly chart for 20 consecutive singles since their debut single |publisher=tokyohive.com |date=2013-02-12 |accessdate=2013-10-09}}</ref>\n\nIn October 2013, Koki Tanaka was removed from the band and the talent agency for having violated his contract, leaving KAT-TUN as a four-man ensemble.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://hochi.yomiuri.co.jp/entertainment/news/20131009-OHT1T00143.htm |title=\u7530\u4e2d\u8056\u3068\u5c02\u5c5e\u5951\u7d04\u89e3\u9664\u3001\uff2b\uff21\uff34\u2015\uff34\uff35\uff2e\u8131\u9000\uff1a\u82b8\u80fd\uff1a\u30b9\u30dd\u30fc\u30c4\u5831\u77e5 |publisher=Hochi.yomiuri.co.jp |date=2013-10-09 |accessdate=2013-10-09 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131017011753/http://hochi.yomiuri.co.jp/entertainment/news/20131009-OHT1T00143.htm |archivedate=2013-10-17 }}</ref>\n\nThe mini album \"Kusabi\" was released on November 27, 2013, on J-Storm. The title track \"Kusabi\" was used as the theme song for the drama ''Henshin Interviewer no Y\u016butsu'' starring KAT-TUN member [[Yuichi Nakamaru]] and actress [[Fumino Kimura]], while \"Gimme Luv\" was used in a Suzuki Solio Bandit television commercial. \"Kusabi\" debuted at the number one spot top the [[Oricon]] weekly album chart, selling approximately 168,000 copies in its first week of release. The album is KAT-TUN's seventh consecutive album to achieve number one, putting them in a tie with singer [[Hikaru Utada]] for most consecutive album number ones in Oricon chart history.<ref name=\"chart\">{{cite web|title=\u3010\u30aa\u30ea\u30b3\u30f3\u3011KAT-TUN\u30011st\u30a2\u30eb\u30d0\u30e0\u304b\u30897\u4f5c\u9023\u7d9a\u9996\u4f4d\u3000\u5b87\u591a\u7530\u306b\u4e26\u3076\u6b74\u4ee31\u4f4d\u30bf\u30a4|url=http://www.oricon.co.jp/news/2031527/full/|publisher=[[Oricon]]|date=2013-12-03|accessdate=2013-12-03|language=Japanese}}</ref>\n\n===2014: ''Come Here''===\n\"In Fact\" was their 22nd single released on June 4, 2014 under the label [[J Storm|J-One Records]]. The title track \"In Fact\" was the main theme song for the TV drama series \"First Class\". In Fact debuted at the number one spot top the Oricon weekly single chart, selling over 146,000 copies in its first week of release. With this, KAT-TUN achieved their 22nd consecutive No.1 with their 22nd single.\n\nOn June 25, \"Come Here\" album was released and KAT-TUN became the first artist in history to have 8 consecutive No.1 albums since debut according to Oricon.<ref>{{cite web|title= \u3010\u30aa\u30ea\u30b3\u30f3\u3011KAT-TUN\u3001\u53f2\u4e0a\u521d\u306e\u5feb\u6319\u30001st\u304b\u30898\u4f5c\u9023\u7d9a\u30a2\u30eb\u30d0\u30e01\u4f4d |url=http://www.oricon.co.jp/news/2039257/full/}}</ref>\n\n===2015: \"Dead or Alive\" single and Taguchi Junnosuke's departure===\n\"Dead or Alive\" was released on January 21, 2015 and it debuted at the number one spot on the Oricon weekly single chart, selling over 192,000 copies in its first week of release. With this, KAT-TUN has then achieved their 23rd consecutive No.1 with their 23rd single. They are currently behind KinKi Kids who are with 34 consecutive No.1 singles since debut.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.oricon.co.jp/| title=\u9031\u9593\u3000CD\u30b7\u30f3\u30b0\u30eb\u30e9\u30f3\u30ad\u30f3\u30b0 2015\u5e7402\u670802\u65e5\u4ed8 | publisher=[[Oricon]] | language=Japanese |  accessdate=March 3, 2017 | archiveurl=http://www.oricon.co.jp/rank/js/w/2015-02-02/ | archivedate=February 2, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.oricon.co.jp/| title=\u3010\u30aa\u30ea\u30b3\u30f3\u3011KAT-TUN\u3001\u30c7\u30d3\u30e5\u30fc\u304b\u308923\u4f5c\u9023\u7d9a1\u4f4d | publisher=[[Oricon]] | language=Japanese |  accessdate=March 3, 2017 | archiveurl=http://www.oricon.co.jp/news/2047752/full/| archivedate=January 27, 2015}}</ref><ref>[http://www.tokyohive.com/article/2015/01/kat-tun-achieve-their-23rd-consecutive-no1-single KAT-TUN achieve their 23rd consecutive No.1 single]</ref>\n\nOn November 24, 2015, before their performance at Best Artist, Junnosuke Taguchi surprised the audience by announcing that he had decided to quit not only KAT-TUN but also from Johnny's Entertainment and that he would retire from the industry by Spring the following year.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.oricon.co.jp/| title=KAT-TUN\u7530\u53e3\u6df3\u4e4b\u4ecb\u3001\u6765\u6625\u306b\u8131\u9000\u3068\u4e8b\u52d9\u6240\u9000\u6240\u3092\u751f\u5831\u544a\u3010\u30b3\u30e1\u30f3\u30c8\u5168\u6587\u3011 | publisher=[[Oricon]] | language=Japanese |  accessdate=March 3, 2017 | archiveurl=http://www.oricon.co.jp/news/2062807/full/ | archivedate=November 24, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.oricon.co.jp/| title=\u30b8\u30e3\u30cb\u30fc\u30ba\u4e8b\u52d9\u6240\u304c\u7530\u53e3\u306e\u9000\u6240\u3092\u767a\u8868 KAT-TUN\u89e3\u6563\u306f\u5426\u5b9a | publisher=[[Oricon]] | language=Japanese |  accessdate=March 3, 2017 | archiveurl=http://www.oricon.co.jp/news/2062785/full/ | archivedate=November 24, 2015}}</ref>\n\n=== 2016: 10th anniversary and Hiatus ===\nKAT-TUN released two more singles as a four-member group entitled \"Tragedy\" on February 10, 2016 followed by \"Unlock\" on March 2, 2016, both of which had reached number 1 in Oricon chart in their first week.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.oricon.co.jp/| title=\u9031\u9593\u3000CD\u30b7\u30f3\u30b0\u30eb\u30e9\u30f3\u30ad\u30f3\u30b0 2016\u5e7402\u670822\u65e5\u4ed8 | publisher=[[Oricon]] | language=Japanese |  accessdate=March 3, 2017 | archiveurl=http://www.oricon.co.jp/rank/js/w/2016-02-22/ | archivedate=February 22, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.oricon.co.jp/| title=\u9031\u9593\u3000CD\u30b7\u30f3\u30b0\u30eb\u30e9\u30f3\u30ad\u30f3\u30b0 2016\u5e7403\u670814\u65e5\u4ed8 | publisher=[[Oricon]] | language=Japanese |  accessdate=March 3, 2017 | archiveurl=http://www.oricon.co.jp/rank/js/w/2016-03-14/ | archivedate=March 14, 2016}}</ref> A compilation album entitled ''\"KAT-TUN 10th Anniversary BEST 10Ks\"'' and a 3-Dome Tour entitled ''\"KAT-TUN 10th Anniversary LIVE TOUR 10Ks\"'' were announced by the three remaining members through their official website.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.oricon.co.jp/ | title=KAT-TUN 10\u5468\u5e74\u30d9\u30b9\u30c8\u76e4&3\u4eba\u4f53\u5236\u3067\u521d\u306e\u30c9\u30fc\u30e0\u30c4\u30a2\u30fc\u6c7a\u5b9a\u3010\u30e1\u30f3\u30d0\u30fc\u30b3\u30e1\u30f3\u30c8\u5168\u6587\u3011| publisher=[[Oricon]] | language=Japanese |  accessdate=March 3, 2017 | archiveurl=http://www.oricon.co.jp/news/2066645/full/ | archivedate=February 10, 2016}}</ref> They also announced that the group activities of KAT-TUN will be on a temporary, indefinite hiatus (or so-called \"recharging period\") starting on May 1, 2016, as each member will focus more on their solo projects and works.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.oricon.co.jp/ | title=KAT-TUN\u30015\u6708\u304b\u3089\u5145\u96fb\u671f\u9593\u3078 \u4e80\u68a8\u548c\u4e5f\u300c\u89e3\u6563\u3067\u306f\u306a\u304f\u3001\u5c06\u6765\u3001\u672a\u6765\u306e\u305f\u3081\u300d| publisher=[[Oricon]] | language=Japanese |  accessdate=March 3, 2017 | archiveurl=http://www.oricon.co.jp/news/2066795/full/ | archivedate=February 13, 2016}}</ref> \u2033''KAT-TUN 10th Anniversary BEST \u201c10Ks\u201d''\u2033 album was then released on March 22, 2016 (the same date with their debut album released back in 2006) and has reached number 1 in the Oricon chart in its first week.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.oricon.co.jp/| title=\u9031\u9593\u3000CD\u30b7\u30f3\u30b0\u30eb\u30e9\u30f3\u30ad\u30f3\u30b0 2016\u5e7404\u670804\u65e5\u4ed8 | publisher=[[Oricon]] | language=Japanese |  accessdate=March 3, 2017 | archiveurl=http://www.oricon.co.jp/rank/ja/w/2016-04-04/ | archivedate=April 4, 2016}}</ref> On August 17, 2016, KAT-TUN released the DVD for KAT-TUN 10TH ANNIVERSARY LIVE TOUR\"10Ks!\u201d and it reached the number one spot in the Oricon Chart as well.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.oricon.co.jp/| title=\u3010\u30aa\u30ea\u30b3\u30f3\u3011KAT-TUN\u3001\u5145\u96fb\u524d\u30e9\u30b9\u30c8\u30e9\u30a4\u30d6\u304cDVD\u7dcf\u54081\u4f4d | publisher=[[Oricon]] | language=Japanese |  accessdate=March 3, 2017 | archiveurl=http://www.oricon.co.jp/news/2077217/full/ | archivedate=August 24, 2016}}</ref>\n\n===2017: Recharging Period and Start of Individual Projects===\nWhile the group activities are temporarily on hold, each member had their own individual projects, apart from the regular TV programs where they were regulars individually. All had been part or starred in different dramas, movies and theatrical plays and all three also had the chance to perform in a concert and stage shows.\n \n===2018: End of Recharging Period and Resume of Group Activities===\nOn January 1, 2018 on the annual Johnny's Countdown, a big surprise had been announced and that KAT-TUN had finally resumed their group activities. The group sang their debut song, Real Face, which was then followed by their new song \"Ask Yourself\" which will be the main theme song for Kamenashi's drama this January. After the performance, the group also announced that concert dates had been decided, which would be happening on April 20\u201322, 2018.<ref>{{cite web|title=KAT-TUN\u3001\u5143\u65e5\u306b\u6d3b\u52d5\u518d\u958b \u300e\u30ab\u30a6\u30b3\u30f3\u300f3\u4eba\u3067\u300cReal Face\u300d\u71b1\u5531|url=https://www.oricon.co.jp/news/2103432/full/|website=Oricon|accessdate=2018-01-01}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=\u30b8\u30e3\u30cb\u30fc\u30ba\u30ab\u30a6\u30f3\u30c8\u30c0\u30a6\u30f3\u306b114\u4eba\u304c\u96c6\u7d50 KAT-TUN\u518d\u59cb\u52d5\u306b\u6b53\u559c|url=https://www.oricon.co.jp/news/2103433/full/|website=Oricon|accessdate=2018-01-01|language=Japanese}}</ref> The group later announced they would be releasing ''CAST'' on 18 July, their first original album in four years.<ref>{{cite news |title=Arama Japan |url=http://aramajapan.com/news/music/kat-tun-to-release-their-first-original-album-in-4-years-titled-cast/89052/}}</ref>\n\n==Current members==\n<!-- DO NOT add Jin Akanishi to this list. Sources posted below have indicated that he has left the group and adding Akanishi to the list or removing the sources will be viewed as vandalism-->\n*{{nihongo|Kazuya '''KA'''menashi|\u4e80\u68a8 \u548c\u4e5f|Kamenashi Kazuya}} (born February 23, 1986)\n*{{nihongo|'''T'''a'''t'''suya '''U'''eda|\u4e0a\u7530 \u7adc\u4e5f|Ueda Tatsuya}} (born October 4, 1983)\n*{{nihongo|Yuichi '''N'''akamaru|\u4e2d\u4e38 \u96c4\u4e00|Nakamaru Yuichi}} (born September 4, 1983)<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.johnnys-net.jp/j/artists/kattun/prof/prof.html |title=KAT-TUN Profile |access-date=2011-03-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160124060541/http://www.johnnys-net.jp/j/artists/kattun/prof/prof.html |archive-date=2016-01-24 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n===Former members===\n<!-- DO NOT remove Jin Akanishi from this list. Sources posted below have indicated that he has left the group and removing Akanishi from the list or removing the sources will be viewed as vandalism-->\n*{{nihongo|Jin '''A'''kanishi|\u8d64\u897f \u4ec1|Akanishi Jin}} (born July 4, 1984)<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.johnnys-net.jp/j/artists/j_akanishi/prof/prof.html |title=Akanishi Jin Profile |access-date=2011-03-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304110546/http://www.johnnys-net.jp/j/artists/j_akanishi/prof/prof.html |archive-date=2016-03-04 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n*{{nihongo|Koki '''T'''anaka|\u7530\u4e2d \u8056|Tanaka K\u014dki}} (born November 5, 1985)\n*{{nihongo|Junnosuke '''T'''aguchi|\u7530\u53e3 \u6df3\u4e4b\u4ecb|Taguchi Junnosuke}}  (born November 29, 1985)\n\n==Discography==\n{{main|KAT-TUN discography}}\n* ''[[Best of KAT-TUN]]'' (2006)\n* ''[[Cartoon KAT-TUN II You]]'' (2007)\n* ''[[KAT-TUN III: Queen of Pirates]]'' (2008)\n* ''[[Break the Records: By You & for You]]'' (2009)\n* ''[[No More Pain]]'' (2010)\n* ''[[Chain (KAT-TUN album)|Chain]]'' (2012)\n* ''[[Come Here (KAT-TUN album)|Come Here]]'' (2014)\n* ''Cast'' (2018)\n* ''Ignite'' (2019)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.j-storm.co.jp/kat-tun/discography/ignite|title=IGNITE {{!}} KAT-TUN \u30aa\u30d5\u30a3\u30b7\u30e3\u30eb\u30b5\u30a4\u30c8|publisher=[[J Storm]]|accessdate=August 6, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Other activities==\n\n===TV shows===\nKAT-TUN had regularly appeared on NHK's [[Johnny's Jr.]] show [[Shounen Club]] and became the regular hosts and leaders of the show until 2006 when they made their official debut. They also became part of other variety programs like ''Minna no Terebi'' and ''KAT-TUNx3''. KAT-TUN even became special supporters for the ''FIVB World Grand Champions Cup'' in 2005, wherein their song \"Gloria\" served as its theme song.\n\nFrom 2005 to January 2007, KAT-TUN was a regular participant in the variety show ''[[Utawara Hot Hit 10]]'' with [[Jun Matsumoto]]. From October 8, 2006, members Tanaka Koki & Nakamaru Yuichi hosted the show [[YouTachi! YOU\u305f\u3061!]] together, until the show ended on September 30, 2007.\n\nFrom April 4, 2007, KAT-TUN then began hosting their own talk show ''[[Cartoon KAT-TUN]]'' every Wednesday until March 24, 2010, comprising a total of 152 episodes. This was their last regular show as a 6-member group.\n\nAfter becoming a 5-member group, their next TV show titled ''KAT-TUN no Zettai Manetaku Naru TV'' began on October 18, 2011 on [[Nippon TV|NTV]] and lasted only for a total of 10 episodes, with the show's finale on December 20, 2011.<ref>{{cite web|title=KAT-TUN\u306e\u7d76\u5bfe\u30de\u30cd\u305f\u304f\u306a\u308bTV|url=http://www.ntv.co.jp/kzm/index.html|accessdate=3 March 2017|language=Japanese|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160407193359/http://www.ntv.co.jp/kzm/index.html|archivedate=7 April 2016}}</ref>\n\nKAT-TUN then also had a one-off TV special titled ''KAT-TUN no Sekaiichi Dame Yoru Ni'' which was aired on the night of January 1, 2012 on [[TBS Television|TBS]]. It was soon followed by another special episode on April 3, 2012. Following the success of the two special episodes of the show, it became KAT-TUN's third regular TV show. The show was then renamed as ''KAT-TUN Sekaiichi Dame na Yoru!'' and began airing from August 24, 2012 until December 28, 2012.<ref>{{cite web|title=KAT-TUN\u306e\u4e16\u754c\u4e00\u30c0\u30e1\u306a\u591c\uff01|url=http://www.tbs.co.jp/kat-tun_dameyoru/|accessdate=3 March 2017|language=Japanese}}</ref>\n\nOn January 11, 2014, after becoming a four-man group, KAT-TUN became guests for a special program titled ''KAT-TUN Sekaiichi Tame ni Naru Tabi'' where they traveled to Okinawa (for two episodes), Aomori, Hokkaido and Kumamoto.  The 5-part special became a success that the show was soon confirmed to become another regular show for KAT-TUN, retaining the same title of the program. The first episode aired on April 17, 2015 and lasted until the 42nd episode on March 25, 2016.<ref>{{cite web|title=KAT-TUN\u306e\u4e16\u754c\u4e00\u30bf\u30e1\u306b\u306a\u308b\u65c5\uff01|url=http://www.tbs.co.jp/tametabi/|accessdate=3 March 2017|language=Japanese}}</ref>\n\nIn 2014, KAT-TUN also became the main hosts for the ''[[Shounen Club]] Premium'', replacing Taichi Kokubun from TOKIO. Their stint as the show's main hosts started from April 2014 until March 2016. Another Johnny's group [[NEWS (band)|NEWS]] then replaced them as the hosts of the show.<ref>{{cite news|title=KAT-TUN\u30014\u4eba\u4f53\u5236\u3067\u521d\u30ec\u30ae\u30e5\u30e9\u30fc \u300e\u30b6\u5c11\u5e74\u5036\u697d\u90e8\u30d7\u30ec\u30df\u30a2\u30e0\u300f\u65b0MC\u306b|url=http://www.oricon.co.jp/news/|accessdate=3 March 2017|archiveurl=http://www.oricon.co.jp/news/2035319/full/|archivedate=19 March 2014|language=Japanese}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|script-title=ja:\uff2b\uff21\uff34\uff0d\uff34\uff35\uff2e\u300c\u30b6\u5c11\u5e74\u5036\u697d\u90e8\u300d\uff13\u6708\u5352\u696d\u3092\u767a\u8868|url=http://www.nikkansports.com/entertainment/news/|accessdate=3 March 2017|publisher=Nikkan Sports News|archiveurl=http://www.nikkansports.com/entertainment/news/1605766.html|archivedate=17 February 2016|language=Japanese}}</ref>\n\n===Radio===\nThe group has had three different radio shows, each hosted by different members and all have aired for several years.\n\nFormer members Jin Akanishi, Koki Tanaka and Junnosuke Taguchi hosted ''KAT-TUN Style'' together from April 2006 until March 2012. Yuichi Nakamaru and Tatsuya Ueda hosted ''R-One KAT-TUN'' every Tuesday from 12am \u2013 12:30am.\n\nKazuya Kamenashi had his own radio show called ''Kamenashi Kazuya - Kase by Kase'' until it ended on September 20. He has a new radio show called ''Kamenashi Kazuya - Hang Out'' and currently airs every Saturday from 10:20am \u2013 10:50am.\n\nTaguchi Junnosuke also had his own radio show called \"Tag-tune driving\" and a radio show together with Yuichi Nakamaru called \"KAT-TUN no Gats\u016bn\" from April 2012 and ended in March 2016.\n\n===Musicals===\nAs a group, KAT-TUN has appeared in [[Koichi Domoto]]'s ''[[Shock (musical)|Shock]]'' musical, ''Summary of Johnnys World'' with NEWS and [[Ya-ya-yah]] and Johnny's long-running ''Dream Boys'' musicals from 2004 to 2006.\n\nSince 2004, member Kazuya Kamenashi has played the lead role in ''Dream Boys'' musicals consecutively each year, after senior [[Hideaki Takizawa]] handed down the role to Kamenashi.\nKamenashi and fellow KAT-TUN member Koki Tanaka paired up to play the lead roles for the shows held in 2007 and 2008. The pair collaborated once again as the leads for the 2011 shows alongside fellow KAT-TUN member Yuichi Nakamaru. The 2012 shows for the musical began in September, and once again Kamenashi reprised his role as the lead for the musical.\n\n===Concerts===\nSince their first concert in 2002, granted after overwhelming numbers of fan requests to Johnny's, KAT-TUN regularly holds concerts during almost every season of the year in Japan. This has helped them gain more popularity with their fans. It was considered remarkable for a Johnny's group which had not yet officially debuted to be able to hold its own concerts.\n\nKAT-TUN was the first Japanese artist to perform for four days in a row at Tokyo Dome during their ''Queen of Pirates'' tour. The following year, they broke their own record becoming the first artists ever to perform for eight consecutive days at Tokyo Dome during their ''Break The Records: By You & For You 2009'' tour. Now, Johnny & Associates submitted this new record to [[Guinness Book of World Records]] for KAT-TUN to be recognized as the Japanese boy band who broke the records in Tokyo Dome performances.<ref name=\"guinness\">{{cite web|title=KAT-TUN concerts may qualify for Guinness|url=http://www.tokyograph.com/news/id-4850}}</ref>\n\nThe group (excluding Jin Akanishi) held their biggest ever concert tour in 2010 titled ''KAT-TUN -NO MORE PAI\u0418- WORLD TOUR 2010'' which consisted of concerts in many major cities across Japan. The tour also included concerts held in Taiwan and Korea; the first time the group has ever toured outside Japan for their official concerts. \nAlthough during their pre-debut years, KAT-TUN had on several occasions toured overseas with their senior groups, while they were still Johnny Jrs.\n\nTheir nationwide tour for 2012 titled ''KAT-TUN LIVE TOUR 2012 CHAIN'' began in Nagiita on Feb 11, they toured 12 cities across Japan including Sendai; which was one of the worst affected areas by the Tohoku earthquake & tsunami disaster back in March 2011.\n\n===Commercials===\nKAT-TUN regularly appeared in TV commercials to endorse for [[NTT docomo]], [[SKY PerfecTV!]], [[Rohto Pharmaceutical Co.|Rohto]] and [[Lotte (conglomerate)|Lotte]] from 2005 to 2009.\n\nSince 2010, member Kazuya Kamenashi endorses [[Panasonic Corporation|Panasonic]]'s Lamdash shaver and DOLTZ electric toothbrush, and [http://www.aoki-style.com/ AOKI] 3D slim suits. Kamenashi also endorses [http://www.beverage.co.jp/gogo/ KIRIN]'s 'Gogo no Kocha' tea since March 2012, and is endorsing [http://sours.jp/ SOURS Gummies] since early 2013.\n\nSince early 2011, the group together has endorsed [[Suzuki]]'s 'SOLIO' car, and has sung commercial theme songs for [http://www.sofina.co.jp/ Sofina] and Wing products. The group are also currently endorsing the mobile game site [https://web.archive.org/web/20120207133710/http://logtomo.jp/ entag!].\n\n===Events===\nOn August 26\u201327, 2006 KAT-TUN members were the main personality supporters for the NTV [[Telethon#Japan|telethon]] ''24 Hour Television: Love Saves the Earth'' charity program.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.oricon.co.jp/news/undefined/28119|title=KAT-TUN\u3001\u7be0\u539f\u6dbc\u5b50\u3089\u300e24\u6642\u9593\u30c6\u30ec\u30d3\u300f\u3067\"\u7d46\"\u3092\u8a34\u3048\u308b\uff01|publisher=[[Oricon]]|accessdate=2010-04-18|language=ja}}</ref>\n\n==Awards==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:650px;\"\n|-\n!align=\"left\"|Years\n!align=\"left\"|Awards\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:center;\"|2006\n|align=\"left\"|\n*[[Japan Gold Disc Award]]s: Music Video Of The Year - ''KAT-TUN Live Kaizokuban''<ref name=\"jpgold2006\">{{cite web|url=http://www.riaj.or.jp/e/data/gdisc/2006.html|title=The 20th Japan Gold Disc Award 2006|publisher=[[Recording Industry Association of Japan|RIAJ]]|accessdate=2010-04-18}}</ref>\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:center;\"|2007\n|align=\"left\"|\n*Japan Gold Disc Awards: Single Of The Year - \"Real Face\"<ref name=\"jpgold2007\">{{cite web|url=http://www.riaj.or.jp/e/data/gdisc/2007.html|title=The 21st Japan Gold Disc Award 2007|publisher=[[Recording Industry Association of Japan|RIAJ]]|accessdate=2010-04-18}}</ref>\n*Japan Gold Disc Awards: The Best 10 Singles - \"Real Face\"<ref name=\"jpgold2007\" />\n*Japan Gold Disc Awards: The Best 10 Singles - \"Signal\"<ref name=\"jpgold2007\" />\n*Japan Gold Disc Awards: The Best 10 Singles - \"Bokura no Machi de\"<ref name=\"jpgold2007\" />\n*Japan Gold Disc Awards: The Best 10 Albums - ''Best of KAT-TUN''<ref name=\"jpgold2007\" />\n*Japan Gold Disc Awards: The Best Music Videos - ''Real Face Film''<ref name=\"jpgold2007\" />\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:center;\"|2008\n|align=\"left\"|\n*Japan Gold Disc Awards: The Best 10 Singles - \"Keep the Faith\"<ref name=\"jpgold2008\">{{cite web|url=http://www.riaj.or.jp/e/data/gdisc/2008.html|title=The 22nd Japan Gold Disc Award 2008|publisher=[[Recording Industry Association of Japan|RIAJ]]|accessdate=2010-04-18}}</ref>\n*Japan Gold Disc Awards: The Best 10 Singles - \"Yorokobi No Uta\"<ref name=\"jpgold2008\" />\n*Japan Gold Disc Awards: The Best Music Videos - ''Live of KAT-TUN \"Real Face\"''<ref name=\"jpgold2008\" />\n*The 17th TV Life Drama Award: Best Theme Song - \"Keep the Faith\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tvlife.jp/drama/2007_d05.php|title=\u6709\u9591\u5036\u697d\u90e8 \u30c9\u30e9\u30de\u3042\u3089\u3059\u3058 TV Life|publisher=TV Life|accessdate=2010-04-18|language=Japanese|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20090725135711/http://www.tvlife.jp/drama/2007_d05.php|archivedate=2009-07-25}}</ref>\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:center;\"|2009\n|align=\"left\"|\n*Japan Gold Disc Awards: The Best 10 Singles - \"Lips\"<ref name=\"jpgold2009\">{{cite web|url=http://www.riaj.or.jp/e/data/gdisc/2009.html|title=The 23rd Japan Gold Disc Award 2009|publisher=[[Recording Industry Association of Japan|RIAJ]]|accessdate=2010-04-18}}</ref>\n*Japan Gold Disc Awards: The Best 10 Singles - \"Don't U Ever Stop\"<ref name=\"jpgold2009\" />\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:center;\"|2010\n|align=\"left\"|\n*Japan Gold Disc Awards: The Best 5 Singles - \"Rescue\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.riaj.or.jp/e/data/gdisc/2010.html|title=The 24th Japan Gold Disc Award 2010|publisher=[[Recording Industry Association of Japan|RIAJ]]|accessdate=2010-04-18}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist|2}}\n\n==External links==\n*[http://www.j-storm.co.jp/kat-tun/ Official page on J-Storm/J-One Records] {{in lang|ja}}\n*[http://www.johnnys-net.jp/page?id=artistTop&artist=14&lang=en_us Official page on Johnny's Website] {{in lang|ja}}\n*{{Allmusic|class=artist|id=p814258|label=KAT-TUN}}\n\n{{KAT-TUN}}\n{{Johnny & Associates}}\n\n{{Authority control}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Kat-Tun}}\n[[Category:Japanese pop music groups]]\n[[Category:Japanese rock music groups]]\n[[Category:Musical groups established in 2001]]\n[[Category:Johnny & Associates]]\n[[Category:Japanese boy bands]]\n[[Category:Japanese idol groups]]\n[[Category:J Storm]]\n[[Category:Musical groups from Tokyo]]\n[[Category:Jin Akanishi]]\n", "text_old": "{{More citations needed|date=April 2009}}\n{{Infobox musical artist <!-- For groups; see Wikipedia:WikiProject_Musicians -->\n| name             = KAT-TUN\n| image            = \n| alt              = \n| caption          = \n| image_size       = \n| background       =  group_or_band\n| alias            = \n| origin           = [[Tokyo]]\n| genre            = {{flatlist| \n* [[J-pop]]\n* [[rock music|rock]]}}\n| years_active     = {{Start date|2001}}\u2013present\n| label            = {{flatlist|\n* [[J Storm|J-One Records]]\n* [[J Storm]]}}\n| associated_acts  = \n| website = {{URL|www.j-storm.co.jp/kat-tun|J Storm}}<br />[https://www.johnnys-net.jp/page?id=artistTop&artist=14&lang=en_us Johnny's Net]\n| current_members  = \n* [[Kazuya Kamenashi]]\n* [[Yuichi Nakamaru]]\n* [[Tatsuya Ueda]]\n| past_members     = \n* [[Jin Akanishi]]\n* [[Koki Tanaka]]\n* [[Junnosuke Taguchi]]\n}}\n\n{{nihongo|'''KAT-TUN'''|\u30ab\u30c8\u30a5\u30fc\u30f3|Kat\u016bn}} is a Japanese [[boy band]] formed under [[Johnny & Associates]] (Johnny's) in 2001. The group's name was originally an acronym based on the first letter of each member's [[family name]]: [[Kazuya Kamenashi|Kazuya '''K'''amenashi]], [[Jin Akanishi|Jin '''A'''kanishi]], [[Junnosuke Taguchi|Junnosuke '''T'''aguchi]], [[Koki Tanaka|Koki '''T'''anaka]], [[Tatsuya Ueda|Tatsuya '''U'''eda]], and [[Yuichi Nakamaru|Yuichi '''N'''akamaru]]. Their debut on March 22, 2006 was marked by a [[wikt:tripartite|tripartite]] release of a [[CD single]], [[album]] and music DVD on their exclusive record label [[J Storm|J-One Records]]. Since then, all of their single, album and music DVD releases have debuted at number one on the ''[[Oricon]]'' music and DVD charts.\n\nIn 2010, Akanishi left the group to start a solo career, making the group's acronym then come from '''KA'''menashi, '''T'''aguchi, '''T'''anaka, '''U'''eda, and '''N'''akamaru, and the group toured with five members.<ref name=\"akanishi_solo\">{{cite web|url=http://www.tokyograph.com/news/id-6357|title=Johnny to remove Akanishi from KAT-TUN|date=2010-07-16|publisher=Tokyograph|accessdate=2010-07-29}}</ref> In 2013, Tanaka's contract was terminated for several violations, leaving KAT-TUN as a four-man ensemble, and '''T'''atsuya '''U'''eda took the T to keep the acronym.<ref name=tanakaout>{{cite web|url=http://natalie.mu/music/news/101091 |title=\u30ca\u30bf\u30ea\u30fc - KAT-TUN\u7530\u4e2d\u8056\u3001\u4e8b\u52d9\u6240\u5951\u7d04\u89e3\u9664\u3067\u30b0\u30eb\u30fc\u30d7\u8131\u9000 |publisher=Natalie.mu |date=2013-10-09 |accessdate=2013-10-09}}</ref> By the end of March 2016, Taguchi left both the group and the agency, leaving KAT-TUN with only three remaining members. The band sold 13,7 million copies in Japan.\n\n==History==\n\n===2001\u20132005: Formation and pre-debut activities===\nBefore becoming KAT-TUN, each member belonged to different [[Johnny's Jr|trainee]] units within Johnny & Associates. In 2001, eight members were chosen to become a temporary dancing unit in order to support [[Koichi Domoto]] in the [[NHK]] music program, ''Pop Jam''. The eight members were switched around before it officially became KAT-TUN, with the current three members plus Jin Akanishi, Koki Tanaka and Junnosuke Taguchi. Although the formation was only meant to be a temporary support unit, KAT-TUN gained a great deal of attention and became a solid unit.<ref>{{cite web|last=Greenburg|first=Adam|url={{Allmusic|class=artist|id=p814258|pure_url=yes}}|title=KAT-TUN: Biography|publisher=[[Allmusic]]|accessdate=2010-04-18}}</ref>\n\nIn 2002, in response to many requests, KAT-TUN held their first concert called {{nihongo|3=Okyaku-sama wa Kami-summer - Concert 55man Nin Ai no Request ni Kotaete!!|2=\u304a\u5ba2\u69d8\u306f\u795e\u30b5\u30de\u30fcConcert 55\u4e07\u4eba\u611b\u306e\u30ea\u30af\u30a8\u30b9\u30c8\u306b\u5fdc\u3048\u3066!!}}, for which 550,000 people tried to get tickets.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cdjapan.co.jp/detailview.html?KEY=JEBN-19|title=Okyakusama wa Kamisama - Concert 55man nin Ai no request ni kotaete!!|publisher=CDJapan|accessdate=2010-04-18}}</ref> That same year, they performed eleven shows in a single day. This is the current record in Japan for the most performances in one day. Since then, KAT-TUN has held concerts in Japan almost every season.\n\nIn 2003-2004, their popularity rose to that of a debuted group, to the point where they performed on [[Music Station]] multiple times before debuting. In 2005, KAT-TUN released their first major DVD, {{nihongo|3=KAT-TUN Live Kaizokuban|2=KAT-TUN Live\u6d77\u8cca\u5e06|4=lit. KAT-TUN Live: Pirate Sails}}, which topped the ''Oricon'' yearly chart for the best-selling DVD. At the 20th [[Japan Gold Disc Award]]s, ''Live Kaizokuban'' placed on the Music Video Of The Year list.<ref name=\"jpgold2006\" />\n\n===2006: Debut and \"Real Face\"===\nOn March 22, KAT-TUN released their debut single \"[[Real Face]]\", accompanied by an album, ''Best of KAT-TUN'' and a DVD ''Real Face Film''. These were released on their own label [[J-One Records]]. The group also went on a nationwide tour, ''Live of KAT-TUN \"Real Face\"'', in support of the album. Within the first week, ''Best of KAT-TUN'', \"Real Face\" and ''Real Face Film'' topped all three ''Oricon'' weekly charts by selling 556,548 copies, 754,234 copies and 374,202 copies respectively.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.oricon.co.jp/news/ranking/16719/|title=KAT-TUN\u30013\u51a0\u9054\u6210\uff01\u30b7\u30f3\u30b0\u30eb\u3001\u30a2\u30eb\u30d0\u30e0\u3001DVD\u3001\u540c\u6642\u5236\u8987\uff01|publisher=[[Oricon]]|accessdate=2010-04-18|language=Japanese}}</ref> They became the second artists to do so, the first being [[Ayumi Hamasaki]]. With these numbers, KAT-TUN holds the record for the highest weekly single debut sales (previously held by [[Arashi]] with their debut single \"[[Arashi (song)|Arashi]]\" of 557,000 copies sold in 1999).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.oricon.co.jp/music/special/060322_02.html|title=KAT-TUN \u6ce8\u76ee\u306e\u30a2\u30fc\u30c6\u30a3\u30b9\u30c8\u9042\u306b\u30c7\u30d3\u30e5\u30fc\uff01|publisher=[[Oricon]]|accessdate=2010-04-18|language=Japanese}}</ref> In addition, \"Real Face\" topped the ''Oricon'' charts for three weeks straight, becoming the first debut single to do so in Japan in 8 years 8 months since [[KinKi Kids]]' debut single \"Garasu no Sh\u014dnen.\"<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.oricon.co.jp/news/ranking/18199/|title=KAT-TUN\u300100\u5e74\u4ee3\u30c7\u30d3\u30e5\u30fc\u30fb\u30a2\u30fc\u30c6\u30a3\u30b9\u30c8\u521d\u306e\u5feb\u6319\u9054\u6210\uff01|publisher=[[Oricon]]|date=2006-04-10|accessdate=2010-04-18|language=Japanese}}</ref> The single sold over a million copies in nine weeks, making \"Real Face\" the highest selling single for the year 2006.<ref name=\"year2006\">[http://www.oricon.co.jp/music/special/061221_02.html ''Oricon'' Ranking 2006] 2006. Retrieved November 10, 2009. {{in lang|ja}}</ref>\n\nIn March 2006, KAT-TUN became the first group to hold their own performances in Japan's most popular stadium, [[Tokyo Dome]], before debuting. They performed to 110,000 people over two days and about 630,000 people in total during the tour. About three months after releasing \"Real Face\", KAT-TUN released their second single, \"[[Signal (KAT-TUN song)|Signal]]\", on July 19.\n\nOn October 12, member Akanishi announced a hiatus from the group in order to study linguistics abroad in the United States, leaving KAT-TUN as a five-member group for six months.<ref>{{cite web|title=KAT-TUN's Jin Akanishi takes break from KAT-TUN; goes to America for English studies|url=http://www.tokyograph.com/news/id-187}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=KAT-TUN's Jin Akanishi back in Japan|url=http://www.tokyograph.com/news/id-928}}</ref> The remaining members continued activities by releasing their third single, \"[[Bokura no Machi de]]\" as the theme song to members Kamenashi and Tanaka's drama, ''[[Tatta Hitotsu no Koi]]'' and their second album, ''Cartoon KAT-TUN II You'' on December 7.\n\nKAT-TUN is the first group in Japan to have all three singles from debut to exceed 500,000 in yearly sales, taking first, fifth and thirteenth place on the Oricon yearly singles chart.<ref name=\"year2006\" />\n\n===2007: ''Cartoon KAT-TUN II You''===\nUnder the same name as their second album, KAT-TUN started their second nationwide tour, ''Tour 2007 Cartoon KAT-TUN II You'', still without Akanishi, on April 3. The next day, KAT-TUN began to host their own variety show ''[[Cartoon KAT-TUN]]'', which aired every Wednesday from 11:55&nbsp;p.m. to 12:26&nbsp;a.m.\n\nAkanishi returned to Japan on April 19 and officially resumed work activities on April 20.<ref>[http://www.tokyograph.com/news/id-928 Tokyograph: Akanishi Back In Japan] April 19, 2007. Retrieved December 18, 2007.</ref> Akanishi joined the rest of KAT-TUN during their tour on April 21 in [[Sendai]] for the encore, marking his official return to KAT-TUN.\n\nOn June 6, KAT-TUN released their fourth single, \"[[Yorokobi no Uta]]\", as the theme song to Tanaka's drama, ''Tokkyu Tanaka 3 Go''.\n\nOn November 21, they simultaneously released their fifth single, \"[[Keep the Faith (KAT-TUN song)|Keep the Faith]]\", as the theme song to members Akanishi and Taguchi's drama, ''[[Yukan Club]]'', and the DVD to their ''Tokyo Dome Live of KAT-TUN \"Real Face\"'' concert. The DVD marked their fifth consecutive release topping the Oricon musical DVD chart, and set the opening week record for the year.<ref>[http://www.oricon.co.jp/news/rankmusic/49982/ ''Oricon'' Style: KAT-TUN\u3001\u65b0\u66f2\u3067\u4eca\u5e74\u306e\u521d\u52d5\u6700\u9ad8\u8a18\u9332\u9054\u6210] November 27, 2007. Retrieved December 23, 2007. {{in lang|ja}}</ref> KAT-TUN took the annual number one position on the Oricon musical DVD charts for the third time in a row with the release.\n\nAfter KinKi Kids, KAT-TUN is the second artist to have all singles since debut to exceed 300,000 in sales during their first week.<ref>[http://www.tokyograph.com/news/id-2141 Tokyograph: KAT-TUN sets 2007 record, L'Arc returns to top] November 6, 2007. Retrieved December 23, 2007.</ref>\n\n===2008: ''Queen of Pirates''===\nKAT-TUN released 'Lips', the theme song to Kamenashi's drama based on the [[manga]] ''[[One Pound Gospel]]'', as their sixth single on February 6.<ref>[http://www.johnnys-net.jp/j/artists/kattun/disco/disco_single.html Johnny's Net: KAT-TUN Discography] {{Webarchive|url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304003005/http://www.johnnys-net.jp/j/artists/kattun/disco/disco_single.html |date=2016-03-04 }} December 21, 2007. Retrieved December 23, 2007. {{in lang|ja}}</ref> The single topped at number one on the Oricon charts.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.oricon.co.jp/search/result.php?kbn=js&types=rnk&year=2008&month=2&week=3&submit4.x=5&submit4.y=19|script-title=ja:2008\u5e7402\u6708\u7b2c3\u9031\u306e\u30b7\u30f3\u30b0\u30eb\u30e9\u30f3\u30ad\u30f3\u30b0\u60c5\u5831|publisher=[[Oricon]]|accessdate=2010-04-18|language=Japanese}}</ref>\n\nKAT-TUN released their seventh single \"[[Don't U Ever Stop]]\" on May 14, which topped the weekly ''Oricon'' chart. On May 15, during the MC segment promoting \"Don't U Ever Stop\" on [[Music Station]], Kamenashi announced that two shows had been added to their Tokyo Dome tourdates, resulting in a total of four consecutive days at the Dome. This marked a historic event in the Dome's history, as KAT-TUN became the first Japanese artist to hold four consecutive days at the stadium since it opened in 1988.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tokyograph.com/news/id-4328|title=KAT-TUN takes over Tokyo Dome for a week|date=2009-01-23|publisher=Tokyograph|accessdate=2010-04-18}}</ref> Other Japanese artists, such as [[SMAP]], [[X Japan]] and [[Ayumi Hamasaki]] have had three consecutive days at the Dome. The Rolling Stones and Michael Jackson have played multiple days at the Dome, but they were not consecutive.\n\nOn June 4, KAT-TUN released their third album, ''[[KAT-TUN III: Queen of Pirates]]''.\n\nOn December 3, KAT-TUN released \"[[White X'mas (song)|White X'mas]]\", their first Christmas single.\n\nOn December 21, it was announced that KAT-TUN would release a new single \"[[One Drop (KAT-TUN song)|One Drop]]\" as a tie-in theme song to Kamenashi's new drama, [[Kami no Shizuku (TV series)|Kami no Shizuku]], just two months after their \"White X'mas\" single. The release consisted of three versions: Limited Edition w/DVD, Regular Edition (First Press) and a Regular Edition.\n\n===2010: International activities, Akanishi's departure and ''No More Pain''===\nOn February 10, KAT-TUN released their first single since March 2009, which was used for Kamenashi's live-action drama adaptation of Tomoko Hayakawa's manga series ''[[Yamato Nadeshiko Shichi Henge]]'', which premiered January 15 on [[Tokyo Broadcasting System|TBS]].<ref>{{cite web|title=Kazuya Kamenashi gets lead role in new TBS winter drama for 2010|url=http://www.tokyograph.com/news/id-5516}}</ref> The single, \"[[Love Yourself (Kimi ga Kirai na Kimi ga Suki)]]\", debuted at number one on the Oricon weekly singles chart, resulting in KAT-TUN's eleventh consecutive number one single since their debut.<ref>{{cite web|title=KAT-TUN's 11th consecutive number one single|url=http://www.tokyograph.com/news/id-5811}}</ref> It became KAT-TUN's first single to sell more than 350,000 copies in its first week since the May 2008 release of their single \"[[Don't U Ever Stop]]\", which sold more than 381,000 copies in its first week.<ref>{{cite web|title=KAT-TUN tops the Oricon weekly charts with their 11th consecutive number one single |url=http://smash.music.yahoo.co.jp/top/20100215-00000032-oric-ent/ }}{{dead link|date=April 2017 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref>\n\nOn March 24, Johnny & Associates announced that KAT-TUN would go on their first Asia concert tour as a five-member group while Akanishi held his own solo concerts in the United States, making him the first Johnny's artist to perform solo in the United States.<ref>{{cite web|title=KAT-TUN 2010 World Tour|url=http://www.sponichi.co.jp/entertainment/news/2010/03/25/01.html|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100327092059/http://www.sponichi.co.jp/entertainment/news/2010/03/25/01.html|archivedate=2010-03-27}}</ref> KAT-TUN is set to have their Asia Tour from early May to late August and although the majority of the concerts will be held in Japan, KAT-TUN will also be heading to Bangkok on July 31, Seoul from August 6 to 7, and Taipei from August 27 to 28; other sources say that a Hawaii concert is also being considered.<ref>{{cite web|title=Jin Akanishi to go to L.A while the rest of the members go on an Asia Tour|url=http://www.tokyograph.com/news/id-5944}}</ref> Due to his absence from KAT-TUN's Asia concert tour and single promotions, Akanishi did not participate in the recording of KAT-TUN's twelfth single \"[[Going!]]\" set for release on May 12.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tokyograph.com/news/id-5989|title=Next KAT-TUN single to lack Akanishi|date=2010-04-06|publisher=Tokyograph|accessdate=2010-04-18}}</ref> Due to the [[2010 Thai political protests|political unrest in Thailand]], Johnny & Associates announced on May 15 that KAT-TUN's concert in Bangkok would be indefinitely postponed.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tokyograph.com/news/id-6104|title=KAT-TUN cancels Bangkok concert|date=2010-05-15|publisher=Tokyograph|accessdate=2010-05-16}}</ref>\n\nKAT-TUN released their first 2010 album, ''[[No More Pain]]'', on June 16 in two versions: a limited and regular edition that both include solo songs by each member.<ref name=\"cdj\">{{cite web|url=http://www.cdjapan.co.jp/detailview.html?KEY=JACA-5224|title=<nowiki>No More Pain [w/ DVD, Limited Edition]</nowiki>|work=CDJapan|accessdate=2010-06-23}}</ref> The limited edition contains thirteen songs and a bonus DVD with the PVs and making-of's the album's songs while the regular edition contains a bonus track.<ref name=\"cdj\" />\n\nJohnny & Associates announced on July 17 that Akanishi would leave the group in late 2010 to pursue a solo career while the rest of the members would continue to work as a five-member group.<ref name=\"akanishi_solo\" /> On July 21, Akanishi himself confirmed through the official Johnny's mobile site, Johnny's Web, that he would leave KAT-TUN to focus on his solo career,<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tokyograph.com/news/id-6372|title=Akanishi comments on leaving KAT-TUN|date=2010-07-20|publisher=Tokyograph|accessdate=2010-07-29}}</ref> although he had not appeared on any event to his fans until October.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.tokyograph.com/news/id-6724|title=Jin Akanishi aims for simultaneous release in U.S., Japan|date=2010-10-03|publisher=Tokyograph|accessdate=2010-10-03}}</ref>\n\nKAT-TUN continued as a group of five. On August 28, the last day of their World Big Tour 2010, KAT-TUN revealed their 2011 tour plan to celebrate their fifth anniversary by performing at industrial complexes in five cities in Japan and expanding its overseas tour to five different countries including Korea, Taiwan, Thailand, China, and Hawaii.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.sanspo.com/geino/news/100828/gng1008280505001-n2.htm|title=\uff2b\uff21\uff34\uff0d\uff34\uff35\uff2e\u4e0a\u7530\u3001\u8131\u81fc\uff01\u6551\u6025\u8eca\u3067\u642c\u9001, Japan|date=2010-08-29|publisher=Sanspo|accessdate=2010-08-30|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100830192231/http://www.sanspo.com/geino/news/100828/gng1008280505001-n2.htm|archivedate=2010-08-30}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://headlines.yahoo.co.jp/hl?a=20100828-00000046-spn-ent |title=\uff2b\uff21\uff34\uff0d\uff34\uff35\uff2e\u3000\u5de5\u696d\u5730\u57df\u3067\u30b3\u30f3\u30b5\u30fc\u30c8\u8a08\u753b\uff1f, Japan |date=2010-08-29 |publisher=Sponichi Annex |accessdate=2010-08-30 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100905230931/http://headlines.yahoo.co.jp/hl?a=20100828-00000046-spn-ent |archivedate=September 5, 2010 }}</ref> The Hawaii concert would make them the first Johnny artist to hold a concert in Hawaii.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://hochi.yomiuri.co.jp/entertainment/news/20100828-OHT1T00023.htm|title=\uff2b\uff21\uff34\u2015\uff34\uff35\uff2e\u3001\u6765\u590f\u306b\u30b3\u30f3\u30d3\u30ca\u30fc\u30c8\u30e9\u30a4\u30d6\u8a08\u753b, Japan|date=2010-08-29|publisher=Yomiuri|accessdate=2010-08-30|language=Japanese|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20100829201650/http://hochi.yomiuri.co.jp/entertainment/news/20100828-OHT1T00023.htm|archivedate=2010-08-29}}</ref> The World Big Tour is where former member Tanaka Koki gave the name \"hyphens\" to the fans, saying that the fans unite KAT-TUN together.\n\nOn October 13, KAT-TUN announced the release of their new single, \"Change Ur World\", which was KAT-TUN's 13th single and the first single after Akanishi's official departure, was released on November 17.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.johnnys-net.jp/j/artists/kattun/disco/_popup/pop_c_ur_w.html|title=Change Ur World Information Page, Japan|date=2010-10-13|publisher=Johnny's net|accessdate=2010-10-25|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101025002329/http://www.johnnys-net.jp/j/artists/kattun/disco/_popup/pop_c_ur_w.html|archive-date=2010-10-25|url-status=dead}}</ref>  The single debuted at number one on the Oricon weekly singles chart for selling 230,829 copies, resulting in KAT-TUN's thirteenth consecutive number one single since their debut plus all of their 13 singles sold over 200,000 copies in the first week.<ref>{{cite web|title=\u3010\u30aa\u30ea\u30b3\u30f3\u3011KAT-TUN\u3001\u30c7\u30d3\u30e5\u30fc\u304b\u308913\u4f5c\u9023\u7d9a\u30b7\u30f3\u30b0\u30eb\u9996\u4f4d, Japan|date=2010-11-23|publisher=Oricon|accessdate=2010-12-03|url=http://www.oricon.co.jp/news/rankmusic/82302/full/?cat_id=tw|language=Japanese}}</ref>\n\nOn December 29, KAT-TUN released KAT-TUN -NO MORE PAI\u0418- WORLD TOUR 2010 DVD, featuring their last day in Japan leg of their successful World Big Tour 2010 at Kyocera Dome and more concert footages from their Korea and Taiwan legs.<ref>{{cite web|title=KAT-TUN -NO MORE PAI\u0418- WORLD TOUR 2010 DVD Information, Japan|date=2010-12-10|publisher=J-Storm|accessdate=2010-12-11|url=http://www.j-storm.co.jp/kat_tun/disco/dvd/d_06.html|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20101208232504/http://www.j-storm.co.jp/kat_tun/disco/dvd/d_06.html|archivedate=2010-12-08}}</ref>\n\n===2011: 5th anniversary===\nThe group announced a release of their 14th single on 2010s Christmas Eve, \"Ultimate Wheels\" on February 2, 2011 along with a tie-in CM of Suzuki Solio car that the group endorsed.<ref>{{cite web|title=Ultimate Wheels Information, Japan|date=2010-12-24|publisher=Johnny's Net|accessdate=2010-12-25|url=http://www.johnnys-net.jp/j/artists/kattun/disco/_popup/pop_ultimate_wheels.html|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20101229080513/http://www.johnnys-net.jp/j/artists/kattun/disco/_popup/pop_ultimate_wheels.html|archive-date=2010-12-29|url-status=dead}}</ref> On January 6, KAT-TUN announced its plan of KAT-TUN Live Tour 2011 during May to October. The tour includes the 5 big dome tour at Sapporo Dome, Tokyo Dome, Nagoya Dome, Yahoo Dome in Fukuoka, and Kyocera Dome in Osaka and a special live event in Kawasaki on July 17\u201319. KAT-TUN will become the fourth Johnny group to be able to conquer the 5 big domes in Japan after SMAP, KinKi Kids and Arashi. After October, the group will start their Asia Tour that includes Thailand, Taiwan, and Korea.<ref>{{cite web|title=\u300c\uff2b\uff21\uff34\u2015\uff34\uff35\uff2e\u300d\u53f2\u4e0a\u521d\u306e\u30b3\u30f3\u30d3\u30ca\u30fc\u30c8\u516c\u6f14, Japan|date=2011-01-06|publisher=Sponichi Annex|accessdate=2011-01-15|url=http://www.sponichi.co.jp/entertainment/news/2011/01/06/01.html|language=Japanese|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110110022732/http://www.sponichi.co.jp/entertainment/news/2011/01/06/01.html|archivedate=2011-01-10}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=\uff2b\uff21\uff34\u2015\uff34\uff35\uff2e\u30e9\u30f3\u30c9\uff01\uff17\u6708\u5ddd\u5d0e\u306b\u51fa\u73fe, Japan|date=2011-01-06|publisher=Yomiuri|accessdate=2011-01-15|url=http://hochi.yomiuri.co.jp/entertainment/news/20110106-OHT1T00038.htm|language=Japanese|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110108193810/http://hochi.yomiuri.co.jp/entertainment/news/20110106-OHT1T00038.htm|archivedate=2011-01-08}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=\uff2b\uff21\uff34\u2010\uff34\uff35\uff2e\u56fd\u5185\u521d\uff01\u30b3\u30f3\u30d3\u30ca\u30fc\u30c8\u30e9\u30a4\u30d6, Japan|date=2011-01-06|publisher=Daily Sports Online|accessdate=2011-01-15|url=http://www.daily.co.jp/gossip/johnnys_topics/2011/01/06/0003720132.shtm|language=Japanese}}{{dead link|date=January 2018 |bot=InternetArchiveBot |fix-attempted=yes }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=\uff2b\uff21\uff34\uff0d\uff34\uff35\uff2e\u521d\u91ce\u5916\u306f\u4eac\u6d5c\u5de5\u696d\u5730\u5e2f, Japan|date=2011-01-06|publisher=Nikkan Sports|accessdate=2011-01-15|url=http://www.nikkansports.com/entertainment/news/p-et-tp0-20110106-721431.html|language=Japanese}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=\u72ac\u9023\u308c\uff2f\uff2b\uff01\uff2b\uff21\uff34\uff0d\uff34\uff35\uff2e\u7279\u5927\u30a4\u30d9\u30f3\u30c8, Japan|date=2011-01-06|publisher=Sanspo|accessdate=2011-01-15|url=http://www.sanspo.com/geino/news/110106/gng1101060505001-n1.htm|language=Japanese|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20110108171236/http://www.sanspo.com/geino/news/110106/gng1101060505001-n1.htm|archivedate=2011-01-08}}</ref> \"Ultimate Wheels\" became their 14th straight No.1 single since their debut. The total number of copies sold in the first week was over 180,000 copies, reported by Oricon. Early March, KAT-TUN announced three new songs in three days, including \"Perfect\" for Kamenashi's new Aoki TV commercial,<ref>{{cite web|title=Perfect song information, Japan|date=2011-03-03|publisher=Johnny's Net|accessdate=2011-03-03|url=http://www.johnnys-net.jp/j/artists/kattun/info_110303.html|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110307220114/http://www.johnnys-net.jp/j/artists/kattun/info_110303.html|archive-date=2011-03-07|url-status=dead}}</ref> \"White\" for a Sofina commercial,<ref>{{cite web|title=Perfect song information, Japan|date=2011-02-18|publisher=Johnny's Net|accessdate=2011-03-03|url=http://www.johnnys-net.jp/j/artists/kattun/info_110218.html|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110219234546/http://www.johnnys-net.jp/j/artists/kattun/info_110218.html|archive-date=2011-02-19|url-status=dead}}</ref> and \"Diamond\" as the theme song of NTV telecasts of Yomiuri Giants baseball games.\n\nIt was announced on March 29 that Johnny's Company would start a new charity project called Marching J, a fundraising project for the Tohoku earthquake victims. The first part of the project started as an event held from April 1 through April 3. From the company, [[SMAP]], [[Tokio (band)|Tokio]], [[KinKi Kids]], [[V6]], [[Arashi]], [[Tackey and Tsubasa]], [[News (band)|NEWS]], [[Kanjani8]], KAT-TUN, [[Hey! Say! JUMP]] and some Johnny's Juniors participated in this first event. The first event will be held at Tokyo, in front of the first Yoyogi gymnasium. Groups took turns according to their schedule and will have a talk session in front of the fans, also calling out for donations for the earthquake victims. And due to this disaster, all the planned events to celebrate KAT-TUN's 5th debut anniversary were cancelled.\n\nOn May 18, KAT-TUN's 15th single, \"White\", was released with \"Perfect\" as its coupling song. By this time, they also announced another two new songs, \"Cosmic Child\" for a Wing TV commercial,<ref>{{cite web|title=Cosmic Child song information, Japan|date=2011-05-17|publisher=Johnny's Net|accessdate=2011-05-17|url=http://www.johnnys-net.jp/j/artists/kattun/info_110511.html|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110516053023/http://www.johnnys-net.jp/j/artists/kattun/info_110511.html|archive-date=2011-05-16|url-status=dead}}</ref> and \"Run For You\" for a New Suzuki Solio commercial.<ref>{{cite web|title=Run For You song information, Japan|date=2011-02-17|publisher=Johnny's Net|accessdate=2011-05-17|url=http://www.johnnys-net.jp/j/artists/kattun/index.html|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20100521154302/http://www.johnnys-net.jp/j/artists/kattun/index.html|archive-date=2010-05-21|url-status=dead}}</ref> On May 29, KAT-TUN with all its five members joined another Marching J project, \"Johnny's Charity Baseball Tournament\" with other Johnny artists and juniors at Tokyo Dome, in which the ticket sales would be donated for Japan's earthquake and tsunami victims.<ref>{{cite web|title=Johnny's Charty Baseball Tournament Information, Japan|date=2011-05-28|publisher=Johnny's Net|accessdate=2011-05-28|url=http://www.johnnys-net.jp/j/artists/kattun/consta/consta.html|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20110524191212/http://www.johnnys-net.jp/j/artists/kattun/consta/consta.html|archive-date=2011-05-24|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nIt was announced in mid-June that members Kazuya Kamenashi, Koki Tanaka and Yuichi Nakamaru would star in this year's ''Dream Boy'' musicals as the leads, shows will commence from September 3 to 25.<ref>{{cite web|title=KAT-TUN\u3001\"\u52dd\u904b\"\u306b\u6539\u540d!?|date=2011-06-14|publisher=Oricon|accessdate=2011-08-19|url=http://www.oricon.co.jp/news/confidence/88808/full}}</ref>\n\nOn September 8, 2011, it was confirmed that KAT-TUN would host a new TV show titled ''[[KAT-TUN no Zettai Manetaku Naru TV]]'', their first show since ''[[Cartoon KAT-TUN]]'' ended in March 2010. The new show began airing on October 18 on NTV.<ref>{{cite web|title=KAT-TUN to host new variety show|date=2011-09-08|publisher=Tokyograph|accessdate=2011-09-15|url=http://www.tokyograph.com/news/kat-tun-to-host-new-variety-show}}</ref> During the broadcast of the first episode, it was revealed that the show will only air for a limited time until the end of December 2011 with a total of 10 episodes.<ref>{{cite web|title=Zettai Manetakunaru TV air for 10 episodes |date=2011-10-18 |publisher=KTnewsinfo |accessdate=2011-11-01 |url=http://kt-newsinfo.livejournal.com/98288.html |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121119003122/http://kt-newsinfo.livejournal.com/98288.html |archivedate=2012-11-19 }}</ref> \nOn September 30, 2011, KAT-TUN announced their 17th single \"Birth\" as the soundtrack to Kamenashi Kazuya's drama \"Youkai Ningen Bem\" would have been released on November 30. \"Birth\" became their 17th straight No.1 single on the Oricon's weekly chart since their debut.\n\n===2012: ''Chain''===\nKAT-TUN began their new year with an extreme special TV show titled ''KAT-TUN no Sekaiichi Dame Yoru Ni'', a one-off show broadcast on the night of January 1 on TBS. A few weeks later they announced the release of their sixth album, titled ''Chain'', scheduled for releasing on February 22. On January 13, KAT-TUN endorsed the mobile game site Entag which used KAT-TUN's album track \"Smile for You\" as the commercial song and the first-ever KAT-TUN animation, \"Ai wa KAT-TUN\", voiced by KAT-TUN themselves, was launched on The Entag site for a limited period.<ref>{{cite web|title=KAT-TUN\u306e\u30c6\u30ec\u30d3CM\u3068\u30aa\u30ea\u30b8\u30ca\u30eb\u30a2\u30cb\u30e1\u304c\u9650\u5b9a\u914d\u4fe1\u3000\u30e2\u30d0\u30a4\u30eb\u30b2\u30fc\u30e0\u30b5\u30a4\u30c8\"entag!\"\u306e\u30b5\u30fc\u30d3\u30b9\u304c\u9593\u3082\u306a\u304f\u958b\u59cb|date=2012-01-06|publisher=Famitsu|accessdate=2012-01-12|url=http://app.famitsu.com/20120106_19095/}}</ref> On February 11, they kicked off their nationwide tour \"KAT-TUN Live Tour 2012 Chain\". This tour covered 12 cities, including Sendai. The tour started in Niigata and will end in Sendai. They will become the first Johnnys group to perform in the affected areas after the earthquake and tsunami disaster.<ref>{{cite web|title=KAT-TUN LIVE TOUR 2012 CHAIN Information|date=2011-11-26|publisher=Johnny's Net|accessdate=2012-01-12|url=http://www.johnnys-net.jp/j/artists/kattun/consta/consta.html|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20120118060945/http://www.johnnys-net.jp/j/artists/kattun/consta/consta.html|archive-date=2012-01-18|url-status=dead}}</ref> Music Station presented on Jan 13 with a special report for the 'Most Powerful Group BEST 20' which listed the Top 20 most powerful groups of all-time in terms of physical single and album sales, KAT-TUN was listed at number 16 with their five-year debut, 17 singles and 5 albums, together they have sold over 8,450,000 records. Music Station hints to this ranking included the debut single 'Real Face' which became 2006's number 1 selling single and how they managed to hold 8 consecutive concert at Tokyo Dome. Among the groups in Top 20, KAT-TUN is apparently the newest group on the list.<ref>{{cite web|title=KAT-TUN ranks No.16 Most Powerful Group of all-time |date=2012-01-14 |publisher=Kat-tunlove |accessdate=2012-02-09 |url=http://kattunlove.livejournal.com/7518329.html |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120115121714/http://kattunlove.livejournal.com/7518329.html |archivedate=2012-01-15 }}</ref>\n\nKAT-TUN's 6th studio album, \"CHAIN\", reached No.1 on Oricon album ranking on March 5, making them the first male artist in history to have six consecutive No.1 albums ever since the debut. KAT-TUN broke the record for the first time in 24 years and 10 months.<ref>{{cite web|title=KAT-TUN\u306e\u6700\u65b0\u30a2\u30eb\u30d0\u30e0\u9996\u4f4d\u3000\u7537\u6027\u6b4c\u624b\u521d\u306e\u30aa\u30ea\u30b8\u30ca\u30eb1st\u304b\u30896\u4f5c\u9023\u7d9a|date=2012-03-05|publisher=Oricon|accessdate=2012-03-05|url=http://www.oricon.co.jp/news/rankmusic/2007637/full}}</ref> On March 8, it was announced that a second episode of ''KAT-TUN no Sekaiichi Dame Yoru Ni'' will be aired on April 3.<ref>{{cite tweet|user=ori_suta|author=\u30aa\u30ea\u2605\u30b9\u30bf|number=177408904379105281|date=7 March 2012|title=\u300eKAT-TUN\u306e\u4e16\u754c\u4e00\u30c0\u30e1\u306a\u591c\u300f\u7b2c\u4e8c\u5f3e\u306e\u653e\u9001\u304c4\u67083\u65e5\u306b\u6c7a\u5b9a\uff01\u30e1\u30f3\u30d0\u30fc\u306e\u7686\u3055\u3093\u306b\u53d6\u6750\u3057\u3066\u304d\u307e\u3057\u305f\u3002\u7206\u7b11\u306e\u9023\u7d9a\u306e\u30a4\u30f3\u30bf\u30d3\u30e5\u30fc\u3067\u3057\u305f\u3088\u266a\u30aa\u30ea\u2605\u30b9\u30bf\u3067\u306f23\u65e5\u58f2\u306b\u30ed\u30b1\u5bc6\u7740\uff06\u6f14\u51fa\u306e\u30de\u30c3\u30b3\u30a4\u6589\u85e4\u3055\u3093\u3068\u30e1\u30f3\u30d0\u30fc\u306e\u5bfe\u8ac7\u300130\u65e5\u58f2\u3067\u30e1\u30f3\u30d0\u30fc\u306e\u30a4\u30f3\u30bf\u30d3\u30e5\u30fc\u3092\u304a\u5c4a\u3051\uff01\u3010\u30aa\u30ea\u30b9\u30bf\u7de8\u96c6\u90e8\uff0f\u307e\u3061\u3053\u3011}}</ref>\n\nOfficial confirmations for the upcoming 2012 shows for Johnny's long-running ''Dream Boys'' musicals was released, and once again member Kamenashi reprises his role as the main lead for the musical. According to confirmation, the shows will begin in September.<ref>{{cite web|title=Dream Boys 2012 confirmed |date=2012-03-12 |publisher=aramatheydidnt |accessdate=2012-03-14 |url=http://aramatheydidnt.livejournal.com/3521879.html |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20120312095410/http://aramatheydidnt.livejournal.com/3521879.html |archivedate=2012-03-12 }}</ref> On April 20\u201322, KAT-TUN performed at Tokyo Dome as parts of their LIVE TOUR 2012 CHAIN tour. According to news reports, KAT-TUN's original idea \"Flash-Tree\" spotlights was introduced for the first time in Johnny and also Tokyo Dome's 25m moving stage was the longest in Johnny's history.<ref>{{cite web|title=Mezamashi News|date=2012-04-23|publisher=|url=}}</ref>\n\nOn June 27, KAT-TUN released its 18th single ''To The Limit'', which was used as a tie-up song for Suzuki Solio Bandit CM.  On June 29 Music Station reported that KAT-TUN ranked as No.10 best-selling Heisei era's idol with the total sales of 6,661,293 copies from 17 singles. In early August it was announced that KAT-TUN's ''Sekaiichi Dame Yoru Ni'' TV special will be turned into a regular show due to the success of the previous 2 special episodes. The regular show was renamed [[KAT-TUN Sekaiichi dame na yoru!]] and began airing on August 24 on TBS.<ref>{{cite web|title=Info on new KAT-TUN regular TV series |date=2012-08-10 |publisher=aramatheydidnt |accessdate=2012-09-17 |url=http://aramatheydidnt.livejournal.com/4129788.html |archive-url=https://archive.is/20121204005707/http://aramatheydidnt.livejournal.com/4129788.html |url-status=dead |archive-date=2012-12-04 }}</ref>\n\nKAT-TUN's 19th single \"Fumetsu no Scrum\" which was used as the themesong for [[Kanjani8]] member Yasuda Shota's drama [[Dragon Seinendan]], was released on September 12 and sold around 157,000 copies within its first week of release, this gives KAT-TUN their 19th consecutive #1 single since their debut in 2006.<ref>{{cite web|title=KAT-TUN grabs No.1 spot on Oricon weekly chart|date=2012-09-17|publisher=tokyohive|accessdate=2012-09-18|url=http://www.tokyohive.com/2012/09/kat-tun-grabs-no-1-spot-on-oricon-weekly-chart/}}</ref>\nIn November, KAT-TUN achieved their 9th consecutive no.1 music-DVD, and 8th no.1 overall DVD with their live DVD, \"KAT-TUN LIVE TOUR 2012 CHAIN TOKYO DOME.\" The latter achievement puts them at 3rd place among male groups who have done the most no.1 overall DVDs in history after B'z and Mr.Children.<ref>{{cite web|title=KAT-TUN\u304cB\u2019z\u30fbMr.Children\u306e\u8a18\u9332\u306b\u4e26\u3093\u3060!!|date=2012-11-28|publisher=oricon|accessdate=2013-01-13|url=http://onlystar.oricon.co.jp/news/music/1959/|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://archive.is/20130218181747/http://onlystar.oricon.co.jp/news/music/1959/|archivedate=2013-02-18}}</ref>\n\n===2013: Tanaka Koki's departure===\n\"Expose\" sold 155,000 copies in first weeks. With this single, their number of consecutive singles topping the chart has reached 20. KAT-TUN is the second artist to top the single chart for 20 consecutive singles since the debut. It was only achieved by their senior KinKi Kids 8 years and a month ago with \u201cAnniversary\u201d.<ref>{{cite web|author=|url=http://www.tokyohive.com/2013/02/kat-tun-tops-oricon-weekly-chart-for-20-consecutive-singles-since-their-debut-single/ |title=KAT-TUN tops Oricon weekly chart for 20 consecutive singles since their debut single |publisher=tokyohive.com |date=2013-02-12 |accessdate=2013-10-09}}</ref>\n\nIn October 2013, Koki Tanaka was removed from the band and the talent agency for having violated his contract, leaving KAT-TUN as a four-man ensemble.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://hochi.yomiuri.co.jp/entertainment/news/20131009-OHT1T00143.htm |title=\u7530\u4e2d\u8056\u3068\u5c02\u5c5e\u5951\u7d04\u89e3\u9664\u3001\uff2b\uff21\uff34\u2015\uff34\uff35\uff2e\u8131\u9000\uff1a\u82b8\u80fd\uff1a\u30b9\u30dd\u30fc\u30c4\u5831\u77e5 |publisher=Hochi.yomiuri.co.jp |date=2013-10-09 |accessdate=2013-10-09 |url-status=dead |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131017011753/http://hochi.yomiuri.co.jp/entertainment/news/20131009-OHT1T00143.htm |archivedate=2013-10-17 }}</ref>\n\nThe mini album \"Kusabi\" was released on November 27, 2013, on J-Storm. The title track \"Kusabi\" was used as the theme song for the drama ''Henshin Interviewer no Y\u016butsu'' starring KAT-TUN member [[Yuichi Nakamaru]] and actress [[Fumino Kimura]], while \"Gimme Luv\" was used in a Suzuki Solio Bandit television commercial. \"Kusabi\" debuted at the number one spot top the [[Oricon]] weekly album chart, selling approximately 168,000 copies in its first week of release. The album is KAT-TUN's seventh consecutive album to achieve number one, putting them in a tie with singer [[Hikaru Utada]] for most consecutive album number ones in Oricon chart history.<ref name=\"chart\">{{cite web|title=\u3010\u30aa\u30ea\u30b3\u30f3\u3011KAT-TUN\u30011st\u30a2\u30eb\u30d0\u30e0\u304b\u30897\u4f5c\u9023\u7d9a\u9996\u4f4d\u3000\u5b87\u591a\u7530\u306b\u4e26\u3076\u6b74\u4ee31\u4f4d\u30bf\u30a4|url=http://www.oricon.co.jp/news/2031527/full/|publisher=[[Oricon]]|date=2013-12-03|accessdate=2013-12-03|language=Japanese}}</ref>\n\n===2014: ''Come Here''===\n\"In Fact\" was their 22nd single released on June 4, 2014 under the label [[J Storm|J-One Records]]. The title track \"In Fact\" was the main theme song for the TV drama series \"First Class\". In Fact debuted at the number one spot top the Oricon weekly single chart, selling over 146,000 copies in its first week of release. With this, KAT-TUN achieved their 22nd consecutive No.1 with their 22nd single.\n\nOn June 25, \"Come Here\" album was released and KAT-TUN became the first artist in history to have 8 consecutive No.1 albums since debut according to Oricon.<ref>{{cite web|title= \u3010\u30aa\u30ea\u30b3\u30f3\u3011KAT-TUN\u3001\u53f2\u4e0a\u521d\u306e\u5feb\u6319\u30001st\u304b\u30898\u4f5c\u9023\u7d9a\u30a2\u30eb\u30d0\u30e01\u4f4d |url=http://www.oricon.co.jp/news/2039257/full/}}</ref>\n\n===2015: \"Dead or Alive\" single and Taguchi Junnosuke's departure===\n\"Dead or Alive\" was released on January 21, 2015 and it debuted at the number one spot on the Oricon weekly single chart, selling over 192,000 copies in its first week of release. With this, KAT-TUN has then achieved their 23rd consecutive No.1 with their 23rd single. They are currently behind KinKi Kids who are with 34 consecutive No.1 singles since debut.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.oricon.co.jp/| title=\u9031\u9593\u3000CD\u30b7\u30f3\u30b0\u30eb\u30e9\u30f3\u30ad\u30f3\u30b0 2015\u5e7402\u670802\u65e5\u4ed8 | publisher=[[Oricon]] | language=Japanese |  accessdate=March 3, 2017 | archiveurl=http://www.oricon.co.jp/rank/js/w/2015-02-02/ | archivedate=February 2, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.oricon.co.jp/| title=\u3010\u30aa\u30ea\u30b3\u30f3\u3011KAT-TUN\u3001\u30c7\u30d3\u30e5\u30fc\u304b\u308923\u4f5c\u9023\u7d9a1\u4f4d | publisher=[[Oricon]] | language=Japanese |  accessdate=March 3, 2017 | archiveurl=http://www.oricon.co.jp/news/2047752/full/| archivedate=January 27, 2015}}</ref><ref>[http://www.tokyohive.com/article/2015/01/kat-tun-achieve-their-23rd-consecutive-no1-single KAT-TUN achieve their 23rd consecutive No.1 single]</ref>\n\nOn November 24, 2015, before their performance at Best Artist, Junnosuke Taguchi surprised the audience by announcing that he had decided to quit not only KAT-TUN but also from Johnny's Entertainment and that he would retire from the industry by Spring the following year.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.oricon.co.jp/| title=KAT-TUN\u7530\u53e3\u6df3\u4e4b\u4ecb\u3001\u6765\u6625\u306b\u8131\u9000\u3068\u4e8b\u52d9\u6240\u9000\u6240\u3092\u751f\u5831\u544a\u3010\u30b3\u30e1\u30f3\u30c8\u5168\u6587\u3011 | publisher=[[Oricon]] | language=Japanese |  accessdate=March 3, 2017 | archiveurl=http://www.oricon.co.jp/news/2062807/full/ | archivedate=November 24, 2015}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.oricon.co.jp/| title=\u30b8\u30e3\u30cb\u30fc\u30ba\u4e8b\u52d9\u6240\u304c\u7530\u53e3\u306e\u9000\u6240\u3092\u767a\u8868 KAT-TUN\u89e3\u6563\u306f\u5426\u5b9a | publisher=[[Oricon]] | language=Japanese |  accessdate=March 3, 2017 | archiveurl=http://www.oricon.co.jp/news/2062785/full/ | archivedate=November 24, 2015}}</ref>\n\n=== 2016: 10th anniversary and Hiatus ===\nKAT-TUN released two more singles as a four-member group entitled \"Tragedy\" on February 10, 2016 followed by \"Unlock\" on March 2, 2016, both of which had reached number 1 in Oricon chart in their first week.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.oricon.co.jp/| title=\u9031\u9593\u3000CD\u30b7\u30f3\u30b0\u30eb\u30e9\u30f3\u30ad\u30f3\u30b0 2016\u5e7402\u670822\u65e5\u4ed8 | publisher=[[Oricon]] | language=Japanese |  accessdate=March 3, 2017 | archiveurl=http://www.oricon.co.jp/rank/js/w/2016-02-22/ | archivedate=February 22, 2016}}</ref><ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.oricon.co.jp/| title=\u9031\u9593\u3000CD\u30b7\u30f3\u30b0\u30eb\u30e9\u30f3\u30ad\u30f3\u30b0 2016\u5e7403\u670814\u65e5\u4ed8 | publisher=[[Oricon]] | language=Japanese |  accessdate=March 3, 2017 | archiveurl=http://www.oricon.co.jp/rank/js/w/2016-03-14/ | archivedate=March 14, 2016}}</ref> A compilation album entitled ''\"KAT-TUN 10th Anniversary BEST 10Ks\"'' and a 3-Dome Tour entitled ''\"KAT-TUN 10th Anniversary LIVE TOUR 10Ks\"'' were announced by the three remaining members through their official website.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.oricon.co.jp/ | title=KAT-TUN 10\u5468\u5e74\u30d9\u30b9\u30c8\u76e4&3\u4eba\u4f53\u5236\u3067\u521d\u306e\u30c9\u30fc\u30e0\u30c4\u30a2\u30fc\u6c7a\u5b9a\u3010\u30e1\u30f3\u30d0\u30fc\u30b3\u30e1\u30f3\u30c8\u5168\u6587\u3011| publisher=[[Oricon]] | language=Japanese |  accessdate=March 3, 2017 | archiveurl=http://www.oricon.co.jp/news/2066645/full/ | archivedate=February 10, 2016}}</ref> They also announced that the group activities of KAT-TUN will be on a temporary, indefinite hiatus (or so-called \"recharging period\") starting on May 1, 2016, as each member will focus more on their solo projects and works.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.oricon.co.jp/ | title=KAT-TUN\u30015\u6708\u304b\u3089\u5145\u96fb\u671f\u9593\u3078 \u4e80\u68a8\u548c\u4e5f\u300c\u89e3\u6563\u3067\u306f\u306a\u304f\u3001\u5c06\u6765\u3001\u672a\u6765\u306e\u305f\u3081\u300d| publisher=[[Oricon]] | language=Japanese |  accessdate=March 3, 2017 | archiveurl=http://www.oricon.co.jp/news/2066795/full/ | archivedate=February 13, 2016}}</ref> \u2033''KAT-TUN 10th Anniversary BEST \u201c10Ks\u201d''\u2033 album was then released on March 22, 2016 (the same date with their debut album released back in 2006) and has reached number 1 in the Oricon chart in its first week.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.oricon.co.jp/| title=\u9031\u9593\u3000CD\u30b7\u30f3\u30b0\u30eb\u30e9\u30f3\u30ad\u30f3\u30b0 2016\u5e7404\u670804\u65e5\u4ed8 | publisher=[[Oricon]] | language=Japanese |  accessdate=March 3, 2017 | archiveurl=http://www.oricon.co.jp/rank/ja/w/2016-04-04/ | archivedate=April 4, 2016}}</ref> On August 17, 2016, KAT-TUN released the DVD for KAT-TUN 10TH ANNIVERSARY LIVE TOUR\"10Ks!\u201d and it reached the number one spot in the Oricon Chart as well.<ref>{{cite web | url=http://www.oricon.co.jp/| title=\u3010\u30aa\u30ea\u30b3\u30f3\u3011KAT-TUN\u3001\u5145\u96fb\u524d\u30e9\u30b9\u30c8\u30e9\u30a4\u30d6\u304cDVD\u7dcf\u54081\u4f4d | publisher=[[Oricon]] | language=Japanese |  accessdate=March 3, 2017 | archiveurl=http://www.oricon.co.jp/news/2077217/full/ | archivedate=August 24, 2016}}</ref>\n\n===2017: Recharging Period and Start of Individual Projects===\nWhile the group activities are temporarily on hold, each member had their own individual projects, apart from the regular TV programs where they were regulars individually. All had been part or starred in different dramas, movies and theatrical plays and all three also had the chance to perform in a concert and stage shows.\n \n===2018: End of Recharging Period and Resume of Group Activities===\nOn January 1, 2018 on the annual Johnny's Countdown, a big surprise had been announced and that KAT-TUN had finally resumed their group activities. The group sang their debut song, Real Face, which was then followed by their new song \"Ask Yourself\" which will be the main theme song for Kamenashi's drama this January. After the performance, the group also announced that concert dates had been decided, which would be happening on April 20\u201322, 2018.<ref>{{cite web|title=KAT-TUN\u3001\u5143\u65e5\u306b\u6d3b\u52d5\u518d\u958b \u300e\u30ab\u30a6\u30b3\u30f3\u300f3\u4eba\u3067\u300cReal Face\u300d\u71b1\u5531|url=https://www.oricon.co.jp/news/2103432/full/|website=Oricon|accessdate=2018-01-01}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|title=\u30b8\u30e3\u30cb\u30fc\u30ba\u30ab\u30a6\u30f3\u30c8\u30c0\u30a6\u30f3\u306b114\u4eba\u304c\u96c6\u7d50 KAT-TUN\u518d\u59cb\u52d5\u306b\u6b53\u559c|url=https://www.oricon.co.jp/news/2103433/full/|website=Oricon|accessdate=2018-01-01|language=Japanese}}</ref> The group later announced they would be releasing ''CAST'' on 18 July, their first original album in four years.<ref>{{cite news |title=Arama Japan |url=http://aramajapan.com/news/music/kat-tun-to-release-their-first-original-album-in-4-years-titled-cast/89052/}}</ref>\n\n==Current members==\n<!-- DO NOT add Jin Akanishi to this list. Sources posted below have indicated that he has left the group and adding Akanishi to the list or removing the sources will be viewed as vandalism-->\n*{{nihongo|Kazuya '''KA'''menashi|\u4e80\u68a8 \u548c\u4e5f|Kamenashi Kazuya}} (born February 23, 1986)\n*{{nihongo|'''T'''a'''t'''suya '''U'''eda|\u4e0a\u7530 \u7adc\u4e5f|Ueda Tatsuya}} (born October 4, 1983)\n*{{nihongo|Yuichi '''N'''akamaru|\u4e2d\u4e38 \u96c4\u4e00|Nakamaru Yuichi}} (born September 4, 1983)<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.johnnys-net.jp/j/artists/kattun/prof/prof.html |title=KAT-TUN Profile |access-date=2011-03-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160124060541/http://www.johnnys-net.jp/j/artists/kattun/prof/prof.html |archive-date=2016-01-24 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n\n===Former members===\n<!-- DO NOT remove Jin Akanishi from this list. Sources posted below have indicated that he has left the group and removing Akanishi from the list or removing the sources will be viewed as vandalism-->\n*{{nihongo|Jin '''A'''kanishi|\u8d64\u897f \u4ec1|Akanishi Jin}} (born July 4, 1984)<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.johnnys-net.jp/j/artists/j_akanishi/prof/prof.html |title=Akanishi Jin Profile |access-date=2011-03-26 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20160304110546/http://www.johnnys-net.jp/j/artists/j_akanishi/prof/prof.html |archive-date=2016-03-04 |url-status=dead }}</ref>\n*{{nihongo|Koki '''T'''anaka|\u7530\u4e2d \u8056|Tanaka K\u014dki}} (born November 5, 1985)\n*{{nihongo|Junnosuke '''T'''aguchi|\u7530\u53e3 \u6df3\u4e4b\u4ecb|Taguchi Junnosuke}}  (born November 29, 1985)\n\n==Discography==\n{{main|KAT-TUN discography}}\n* ''[[Best of KAT-TUN]]'' (2006)\n* ''[[Cartoon KAT-TUN II You]]'' (2007)\n* ''[[KAT-TUN III: Queen of Pirates]]'' (2008)\n* ''[[Break the Records: By You & for You]]'' (2009)\n* ''[[No More Pain]]'' (2010)\n* ''[[Chain (KAT-TUN album)|Chain]]'' (2012)\n* ''[[Come Here (KAT-TUN album)|Come Here]]'' (2014)\n* ''Cast'' (2018)\n* ''Ignite'' (2019)<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.j-storm.co.jp/kat-tun/discography/ignite|title=IGNITE {{!}} KAT-TUN \u30aa\u30d5\u30a3\u30b7\u30e3\u30eb\u30b5\u30a4\u30c8|publisher=[[J Storm]]|accessdate=August 6, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Other activities==\n\n===TV shows===\nKAT-TUN had regularly appeared on NHK's [[Johnny's Jr.]] show [[Shounen Club]] and became the regular hosts and leaders of the show until 2006 when they made their official debut. They also became part of other variety programs like ''Minna no Terebi'' and ''KAT-TUNx3''. KAT-TUN even became special supporters for the ''FIVB World Grand Champions Cup'' in 2005, wherein their song \"Gloria\" served as its theme song.\n\nFrom 2005 to January 2007, KAT-TUN was a regular participant in the variety show ''[[Utawara Hot Hit 10]]'' with [[Jun Matsumoto]]. From October 8, 2006, members Tanaka Koki & Nakamaru Yuichi hosted the show [[YouTachi! YOU\u305f\u3061!]] together, until the show ended on September 30, 2007.\n\nFrom April 4, 2007, KAT-TUN then began hosting their own talk show ''[[Cartoon KAT-TUN]]'' every Wednesday until March 24, 2010, comprising a total of 152 episodes. This was their last regular show as a 6-member group.\n\nAfter becoming a 5-member group, their next TV show titled ''KAT-TUN no Zettai Manetaku Naru TV'' began on October 18, 2011 on [[Nippon TV|NTV]] and lasted only for a total of 10 episodes, with the show's finale on December 20, 2011.<ref>{{cite web|title=KAT-TUN\u306e\u7d76\u5bfe\u30de\u30cd\u305f\u304f\u306a\u308bTV|url=http://www.ntv.co.jp/kzm/index.html|accessdate=3 March 2017|language=Japanese|url-status=dead|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160407193359/http://www.ntv.co.jp/kzm/index.html|archivedate=7 April 2016}}</ref>\n\nKAT-TUN then also had a one-off TV special titled ''KAT-TUN no Sekaiichi Dame Yoru Ni'' which was aired on the night of January 1, 2012 on [[TBS Television|TBS]]. It was soon followed by another special episode on April 3, 2012. Following the success of the two special episodes of the show, it became KAT-TUN's third regular TV show. The show was then renamed as ''KAT-TUN Sekaiichi Dame na Yoru!'' and began airing from August 24, 2012 until December 28, 2012.<ref>{{cite web|title=KAT-TUN\u306e\u4e16\u754c\u4e00\u30c0\u30e1\u306a\u591c\uff01|url=http://www.tbs.co.jp/kat-tun_dameyoru/|accessdate=3 March 2017|language=Japanese}}</ref>\n\nOn January 11, 2014, after becoming a four-man group, KAT-TUN became guests for a special program titled ''KAT-TUN Sekaiichi Tame ni Naru Tabi'' where they traveled to Okinawa (for two episodes), Aomori, Hokkaido and Kumamoto.  The 5-part special became a success that the show was soon confirmed to become another regular show for KAT-TUN, retaining the same title of the program. The first episode aired on April 17, 2015 and lasted until the 42nd episode on March 25, 2016.<ref>{{cite web|title=KAT-TUN\u306e\u4e16\u754c\u4e00\u30bf\u30e1\u306b\u306a\u308b\u65c5\uff01|url=http://www.tbs.co.jp/tametabi/|accessdate=3 March 2017|language=Japanese}}</ref>\n\nIn 2014, KAT-TUN also became the main hosts for the ''[[Shounen Club]] Premium'', replacing Taichi Kokubun from TOKIO. Their stint as the show's main hosts started from April 2014 until March 2016. Another Johnny's group [[NEWS (band)|NEWS]] then replaced them as the hosts of the show.<ref>{{cite news|title=KAT-TUN\u30014\u4eba\u4f53\u5236\u3067\u521d\u30ec\u30ae\u30e5\u30e9\u30fc \u300e\u30b6\u5c11\u5e74\u5036\u697d\u90e8\u30d7\u30ec\u30df\u30a2\u30e0\u300f\u65b0MC\u306b|url=http://www.oricon.co.jp/news/|accessdate=3 March 2017|archiveurl=http://www.oricon.co.jp/news/2035319/full/|archivedate=19 March 2014|language=Japanese}}</ref><ref>{{cite news|script-title=ja:\uff2b\uff21\uff34\uff0d\uff34\uff35\uff2e\u300c\u30b6\u5c11\u5e74\u5036\u697d\u90e8\u300d\uff13\u6708\u5352\u696d\u3092\u767a\u8868|url=http://www.nikkansports.com/entertainment/news/|accessdate=3 March 2017|publisher=Nikkan Sports News|archiveurl=http://www.nikkansports.com/entertainment/news/1605766.html|archivedate=17 February 2016|language=Japanese}}</ref>\n\n===Radio===\nThe group has had three different radio shows, each hosted by different members and all have aired for several years.\n\nFormer members Jin Akanishi, Koki Tanaka and Junnosuke Taguchi hosted ''KAT-TUN Style'' together from April 2006 until March 2012. Yuichi Nakamaru and Tatsuya Ueda hosted ''R-One KAT-TUN'' every Tuesday from 12am \u2013 12:30am.\n\nKazuya Kamenashi had his own radio show called ''Kamenashi Kazuya - Kase by Kase'' until it ended on September 20. He has a new radio show called ''Kamenashi Kazuya - Hang Out'' and currently airs every Saturday from 10:20am \u2013 10:50am.\n\nTaguchi Junnosuke also had his own radio show called \"Tag-tune driving\" and a radio show together with Yuichi Nakamaru called \"KAT-TUN no Gats\u016bn\" from April 2012 and ended in March 2016.\n\n===Musicals===\nAs a group, KAT-TUN has appeared in [[Koichi Domoto]]'s ''[[Shock (musical)|Shock]]'' musical, ''Summary of Johnnys World'' with NEWS and [[Ya-ya-yah]] and Johnny's long-running ''Dream Boys'' musicals from 2004 to 2006.\n\nSince 2004, member Kazuya Kamenashi has played the lead role in ''Dream Boys'' musicals consecutively each year, after senior [[Hideaki Takizawa]] handed down the role to Kamenashi.\nKamenashi and fellow KAT-TUN member Koki Tanaka paired up to play the lead roles for the shows held in 2007 and 2008. The pair collaborated once again as the leads for the 2011 shows alongside fellow KAT-TUN member Yuichi Nakamaru. The 2012 shows for the musical began in September, and once again Kamenashi reprised his role as the lead for the musical.\n\n===Concerts===\nSince their first concert in 2002, granted after overwhelming numbers of fan requests to Johnny's, KAT-TUN regularly holds concerts during almost every season of the year in Japan. This has helped them gain more popularity with their fans. It was considered remarkable for a Johnny's group which had not yet officially debuted to be able to hold its own concerts.\n\nKAT-TUN was the first Japanese artist to perform for four days in a row at Tokyo Dome during their ''Queen of Pirates'' tour. The following year, they broke their own record becoming the first artists ever to perform for eight consecutive days at Tokyo Dome during their ''Break The Records: By You & For You 2009'' tour. Now, Johnny & Associates submitted this new record to [[Guinness Book of World Records]] for KAT-TUN to be recognized as the Japanese boy band who broke the records in Tokyo Dome performances.<ref name=\"guinness\">{{cite web|title=KAT-TUN concerts may qualify for Guinness|url=http://www.tokyograph.com/news/id-4850}}</ref>\n\nThe group (excluding Jin Akanishi) held their biggest ever concert tour in 2010 titled ''KAT-TUN -NO MORE PAI\u0418- WORLD TOUR 2010'' which consisted of concerts in many major cities across Japan. The tour also included concerts held in Taiwan and Korea; the first time the group has ever toured outside Japan for their official concerts. \nAlthough during their pre-debut years, KAT-TUN had on several occasions toured overseas with their senior groups, while they were still Johnny Jrs.\n\nTheir nationwide tour for 2012 titled ''KAT-TUN LIVE TOUR 2012 CHAIN'' began in Nagiita on Feb 11, they toured 12 cities across Japan including Sendai; which was one of the worst affected areas by the Tohoku earthquake & tsunami disaster back in March 2011.\n\n===Commercials===\nKAT-TUN regularly appeared in TV commercials to endorse for [[NTT docomo]], [[SKY PerfecTV!]], [[Rohto Pharmaceutical Co.|Rohto]] and [[Lotte (conglomerate)|Lotte]] from 2005 to 2009.\n\nSince 2010, member Kazuya Kamenashi endorses [[Panasonic Corporation|Panasonic]]'s Lamdash shaver and DOLTZ electric toothbrush, and [http://www.aoki-style.com/ AOKI] 3D slim suits. Kamenashi also endorses [http://www.beverage.co.jp/gogo/ KIRIN]'s 'Gogo no Kocha' tea since March 2012, and is endorsing [http://sours.jp/ SOURS Gummies] since early 2013.\n\nSince early 2011, the group together has endorsed [[Suzuki]]'s 'SOLIO' car, and has sung commercial theme songs for [http://www.sofina.co.jp/ Sofina] and Wing products. The group are also currently endorsing the mobile game site [https://web.archive.org/web/20120207133710/http://logtomo.jp/ entag!].\n\n===Events===\nOn August 26\u201327, 2006 KAT-TUN members were the main personality supporters for the NTV [[Telethon#Japan|telethon]] ''24 Hour Television: Love Saves the Earth'' charity program.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.oricon.co.jp/news/undefined/28119|title=KAT-TUN\u3001\u7be0\u539f\u6dbc\u5b50\u3089\u300e24\u6642\u9593\u30c6\u30ec\u30d3\u300f\u3067\"\u7d46\"\u3092\u8a34\u3048\u308b\uff01|publisher=[[Oricon]]|accessdate=2010-04-18|language=ja}}</ref>\n\n==Awards==\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:650px;\"\n|-\n!align=\"left\"|Years\n!align=\"left\"|Awards\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:center;\"|2006\n|align=\"left\"|\n*[[Japan Gold Disc Award]]s: Music Video Of The Year - ''KAT-TUN Live Kaizokuban''<ref name=\"jpgold2006\">{{cite web|url=http://www.riaj.or.jp/e/data/gdisc/2006.html|title=The 20th Japan Gold Disc Award 2006|publisher=[[Recording Industry Association of Japan|RIAJ]]|accessdate=2010-04-18}}</ref>\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:center;\"|2007\n|align=\"left\"|\n*Japan Gold Disc Awards: Single Of The Year - \"Real Face\"<ref name=\"jpgold2007\">{{cite web|url=http://www.riaj.or.jp/e/data/gdisc/2007.html|title=The 21st Japan Gold Disc Award 2007|publisher=[[Recording Industry Association of Japan|RIAJ]]|accessdate=2010-04-18}}</ref>\n*Japan Gold Disc Awards: The Best 10 Singles - \"Real Face\"<ref name=\"jpgold2007\" />\n*Japan Gold Disc Awards: The Best 10 Singles - \"Signal\"<ref name=\"jpgold2007\" />\n*Japan Gold Disc Awards: The Best 10 Singles - \"Bokura no Machi de\"<ref name=\"jpgold2007\" />\n*Japan Gold Disc Awards: The Best 10 Albums - ''Best of KAT-TUN''<ref name=\"jpgold2007\" />\n*Japan Gold Disc Awards: The Best Music Videos - ''Real Face Film''<ref name=\"jpgold2007\" />\n|-\n! style=\"text-align:center;\"|2008\n|align=\"left\"|\n*Japan Gold Disc Awards: The Best 10 Singles - \"Keep the Faith\"<ref name=\"jpgold2008\">{{cite web|url=http://www.riaj.or.jp/e/data/gdisc/2008.html|title=The 22nd Japan Gold Disc Award 2008|publisher=[[Recording Industry Association of Japan|RIAJ]]|access